VALUES
	(2926, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Home', 'home', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex row-columns-1-3_2-3 with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large\" style=\"\n    /* margin-top: -50px; */\n\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/anthony-avatar-large-anthony-olsen-1080x675_xmdgo9_ynyj1z_5f2vrU_ouiqt4\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"nm6rkrh3hsip\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div>                        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"w-full uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">﻿BOOK A SESSIOn</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">In the middle of the road of my life, I awoke in a dark wood, where the true way was wholly lost.</blockquote></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p class=\"uppercase text-sm mt-4\" style=\"text-align: right;margin-top:0\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"text-align: right;margin-top:0\">- David Whyte</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\" style=\"\n    margin-top: -50px;\n\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin-top: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 30px;\">I am a Melbourne &amp;&nbsp;﻿Surfcoast&nbsp;based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.</h2>\n<p>I&nbsp;﻿work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Road in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick\">Brunswick</a> and, from February 2026, will also be offering psychotherapy and individual breathwork sessions in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne\">Lorne on the Surf Coast of Victoria</a>. I support people across a wide range of areas, including anxiety, depression, and experiences of spiritual emergence or emergency.</p>\n<p>My work is informed by Gestalt, Process Oriented, and Transpersonal approaches, with roots in Traditional Chinese Medicine. My approach is awareness-based, using the breath and body as central tools to support psychological healing and personal growth. I&nbsp;﻿firmly believe that we can not simply think our way through crisis but we need to learn how to come into relationship with them.</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/about\">Read More about my work →﻿</a>﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Services and Modalities offered</h2>\n<h2>Psychotherapy &amp;&nbsp;﻿Counselling</h2>\n<p>I offer one-on-one psychotherapy and counselling in Brunswick, and from February 2026, in Lorne on the Surf Coast. My work draws on Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal approaches, using mind, body, and awareness-based practices to support psychological healing, personal growth, and more fulfilling relationships.</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/psychotherapy-and-counselling\">﻿Find out more about Psychotherapy &amp;&nbsp;﻿Counselling →</a>﻿﻿</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"my-8\"></figure>\n<h2>Holotropic Breathwork</h2>\n<p>﻿﻿I offer Holotropic Breathwork sessions and workshops that use guided breathing to help people process emotions, increase self-awareness, and support personal growth. Sessions are experiential, safe, and tailored to each person’s needs.﻿<br></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/holotropic-breathwork\">Find out more about Breathwork&nbsp; →</a>﻿﻿</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"my-8\"></figure>\n<h2>Men\'s Groups</h2>\n<p>I facilitate ongoing Men’s Groups to support personal insight, relational growth, and emotional resilience. These groups provide a safe space for men to explore their inner world, build authentic connections, and deepen self-awareness.<br></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/mens-groups\">Find out more about mens Groups&nbsp; →</a></p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure>\n<h2>Upcoming Events</h2>\n<p>I regularly run Holotropic Breathwork workshops and Men\'s Group workshops. You can see the available workshops and events below:</p>\n<div>{%feed|domain:melbournebreathwork.com|model:events|filter:future|layout:calendar%}</div></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-auto uk-flex-top uk-dark padding-extra-large row-columns-1-1\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Resources for therapy</h2></div>\n                        </div>\n                                            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-mode=\"readonly\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\" data-active=\"0\">\n                                    <span data-id=\"3\" data-type=\"Grid\" data-source=\"Pages\" data-parent=\"0\" data-display=\"vertical-card\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\">[widget:3|Grid|Pages]</span>\n                                </div></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo has-section-width-uk-container-large padding-small row-columns-1-4_3-4\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Two practice locations</h2>\n<p>Sessions are available in two locations (from Feb 2026) in&nbsp;Brunswick and Lorne on the surf coast of Victoria.&nbsp;</p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>Brunswick Practice</b></h2>\n<p><b>﻿</b>﻿<b>503 Sydney Rd, Brunwsick, 3056.</b>﻿<b>﻿<br></b></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"9\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"Map\" data-source=\"Clinic Address\">[widget:9|Map|Clinic Address]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>Lorne Practice</b></h2>\n<p><b>6/5 Cora Lynne Crt, Lorne, 3232</b></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3121.452969334028!2d143.9361975759189!3d-38.52332537180633!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x6ad3653a2508d14d%3A0xf36e7ab931454e69!2sUnit%206%2F5%20Cora%20Lynn%20Ct%2C%20Lorne%20VIC%203232!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sau!4v1767311802600!5m2!1sen!2sau\" width=\"900\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe></figure></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 1, '1', '', 'dorin-moise-359008_rbtxt3', 1314, 1, 'I am a Melbourne and Surf Coast based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.\nI work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Rd in Brunswick and cater to people looking for support across a wide range of areas including anxiety, depression, spiritual emergence / emergency and more. \n\nI work from a Gestalt-informed, Process Oriented, and Transpersonal perspective, with roots in Traditional Chinese Medicine. My approach is awareness-based, using the breath and body as central tools to support healing and personal growth.\n\nI am a Melbourne based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.\nI work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Rd in Brunswick and cater to people looking for support across a wide range of areas including anxiety, depression, spiritual emergence / emergency and more', 'Brunswick & Surfcoast Psychotherapy & Counselling', NULL, 'Melbourne and Surf Coast based Psychotherapist and Holotropic Breathwork practitioner offering support for anxiety, depression, and spiritual emergence. Experience healing and personal growth with an awareness-based approach rooted in Traditional Chinese Medicine.', '2025-06-29 11:45:44', '2026-01-07 07:43:22', 0, NULL, 2, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2927, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Appointments', 'appointments', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-50 uk-flex-middle with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large row-columns-1-3\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/andrew-st-lawrence-w0v2678-r-w-unsplash_vqkhgz\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"vgcow0y9z44a\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Sessions now available in two locations</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Wild Heart Psychotherapy offers psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork sessions in <strong>Brunswick (Melbourne)</strong> and <strong>Lorne (Surf Coast), Victoria</strong>. Each location provides a calm and supportive setting for depth-oriented work, with options for in-person or telehealth sessions.﻿<br></p></div>\n</div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/brunswick\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">﻿BOOK A SESSION IN BRUNSWICK</a> <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">BOOK A SESSION IN Lorne</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Brunswick Clinic</h2>\n<p>﻿503 Sydney Rd, Brunswick, Vic 3056.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3154.0530035270726!2d144.95736798729848!3d-37.7653553590327!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x6ad64352bb51a8ff%3A0x1291743c8e1539e5!2s503%20Sydney%20Rd%2C%20Brunswick%20VIC%203056!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sau!4v1767314361402!5m2!1sen!2sau\" width=\"900\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Lorne Clinic</h2>\n<p>6/5 Cora Lynn Crt, Lorne Vic 3232.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3121.4531513581846!2d143.93619757636571!3d-38.523321174923794!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x6ad3653a2508d14d%3A0xf36e7ab931454e69!2sUnit%206%2F5%20Cora%20Lynn%20Ct%2C%20Lorne%20VIC%203232!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sau!4v1767314464980!5m2!1sen!2sau\" width=\"900\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe></figure></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'therapy_ydfwfv', 1314, 1, '', 'Book Your Session: In-Person &amp; Telehealth Appointments in Brunswick', NULL, 'Schedule your 50-min or 1.2-hour session in Brunswick or via telehealth/zoom. Not ready yet? Opt for a free 20-min introductory chat. Also explore one-on-one breathwork sessions.', '2025-06-29 11:52:48', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 0, NULL, 3, NULL, 0, 12, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2928, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Services', 'services', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 padding-small with-redo row-columns-1-4 has-section-width-uk-container\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 style=\"margin-top: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 30px;\">Services</h1></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>At Wild Heart Psychotherapy, I offer a supportive and practical space to talk through what’s happening in your life. People come to therapy for many reasons – feeling stuck or anxious, working through grief or relationship challenges, or wanting to better understand themselves and how they relate to the world.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"10\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"Grid\" data-source=\"Pages\">[widget:10|Grid|Pages]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-3-4_1-4\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                                                            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p>\n<h2><strong>Services include:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>- Individual psychotherapy and counselling</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>- Integration sessions for Holotropic Breathwork or psychedelic experiences</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>- Somatic and creative therapy approaches</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>- Process-oriented and Gestalt therapy</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>- Support for anxiety, depression, grief, and life transitions</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>- Personal development and self-reflection</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 60px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px;\">How I Work</h3>\n<p>My approach is grounded, respectful, and centred around what you need right now. Some sessions may focus on clear goals or specific challenges, while others explore deeper patterns or life questions over time. I draw on different therapeutic frameworks to suit your situation, aiming to make each session a useful step towards greater understanding, relief, or change. If you’re considering therapy, you’re welcome to get in touch to arrange an initial chat or to book a session to begin this work together.</p>\n<p></p></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/anthony-avatar-large-anthony-olsen-1080x675_xmdgo9_ynyj1z_5f2vrU_ouiqt4\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"8gashftgtx23\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_dzpjbc_l83k0a', 1314, 1, '', 'Psychotherapy Services | Wild Heart Psychotherapy', NULL, 'Experience grounded, respectful psychotherapy at Wild Heart Psychotherapy. We offer support for anxiety, depression, grief, and life transitions. Connect today for an initial chat or to book a session.', '2025-06-30 08:15:26', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 0, NULL, 48, NULL, 0, 3, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2929, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Psychotherapy and Counselling', 'psychotherapy-and-counselling', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-40 uk-flex-middle with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3 has-section-width-uk-container-large padding-small\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/mohamed-nohassi-odxB5oIG_iA-unsplash_r49u8y\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"3dytms557z8w\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"w-full uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">﻿BOOK A SESSION</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 60px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px;\">Grief is not a feeling it is a capacity. It is not something that disables you, we are not on the receiving end of grief we are on the practising end of grief.</blockquote></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p class=\"text-xs mt-4 uppercase float-right\">- Stephen Jenkinson</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Psychotherapy &amp; Counselling in Brunswick and the Surf Coast</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">I offer one-on-one counselling and psychotherapy sessions in Brunswick (and Lorne from Feb 2026), working with people who are ready to develop greater awareness, process unresolved experiences, and build better relationships.</h3></div>\n</div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>How I Work</h2>\n<p>My approach draws from Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal methods. These are experiential sessions that include your mind, body, and spirit in addressing whatever you bring. Rather than just talking, we might work with breathing, body awareness, dreams, or other ways of exploring what\'s present for you.</p>\n<p>Each session is shaped by what emerges and what feels most helpful in the moment. Some people find this different from traditional talk therapy, and that\'s intentional—I believe healing happens through the whole person, not just through thinking about problems.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What People Bring to Sessions</h2>\n<p>I work with people experiencing:</p>\n<ul><li>Anxiety and depression</li><li>Trauma and its effects</li><li>Grief and loss</li><li>Physical pain that seems connected to emotional experiences</li><li>Relationship patterns they want to understand or change</li><li>A desire for psychological integration</li><li>Interest in shadow work—exploring parts of themselves they\'ve pushed away</li><li>Simply wanting to explore their inner world more deeply</li><li>Spiritual Emergence and emergency</li><li>Eco-therapy and creating / enhancing connection to nature</li></ul>\n<p>﻿﻿All of these areas are supported at both our Brunswick and Lorne clinics.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>About the Process</h2>\n<p>Sessions are experiential, which means we work with what\'s actually happening in the present moment. This might include noticing body sensations, following your breath, exploring a feeling, or working with imagery. I pay attention to the whole person—not just your words, but how you sit, breathe, and move through the world.</p>\n<p>Some sessions involve breathwork. Others focus on dialogue between different parts of yourself. We might explore dreams, work with creative expression, or simply sit with what\'s present. The approach adapts to what you need.﻿<br></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Location and Community</h2>\n<p><strong>Brunswick:</strong> <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick\">503 Sydney Road</a>, near the corner of Blythe Street. Two-hour parking is available on Sydney Road — please check clearway times to avoid fines.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorne:</strong> <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne\">Our Surf Coast clinic </a>is minutes from the Erskine River rainforest and the beach, with ample parking nearby.</p>\n<p>I see clients from across Melbourne’s inner north, including Brunswick, Fitzroy, Carlton, and Coburg, as well as from the Surf Coast — Torquay, Anglesea, Aireys Inlet, Lorne, Colac, and surrounding areas.﻿</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Getting Started</h2>\n<p>If you\'re curious about this approach or think it might be helpful for what you\'re experiencing, we can start with a conversation. I\'m happy to discuss what you\'re looking for and whether working together makes sense.</p>\n<p>The work requires some openness to exploring beyond just talking, but you don\'t need any special experience or preparation. You just need to be willing to see what emerges when we create space for it,&nbsp;whether working together makes sense in Brunswick or at the Surf Coast Lorne clinic.<br></p></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', 'https://', 'norway_k1dqti', 1314, 1, 'I offer one-on-one counselling and psychotherapy sessions in Brunswick, working with people who are ready to develop greater awareness, process unresolved experiences, and build better relationships.', 'Psychotherapy &amp; Counselling in Brunswick &amp; Surfcoast | Holistic Healing Approach', NULL, 'Offering one-on-one psychotherapy and counselling sessions in Brunswick. Specializing in Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal methods to help you develop greater awareness, resolve past experiences, and improve relationships.', '2025-07-01 00:00:41', '2026-01-13 07:40:19', 48, NULL, 5, NULL, 0, 5, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2930, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork', 'holotropic-breathwork', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3 has-section-width-uk-container padding-none height-auto uk-flex-top\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/meagan-carsience-TpG2TBiclik-unsplash_gy44ix_exacii\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary w-full\">﻿BOOK A SESSION</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 60px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px;\">A powerful breathing technique designed to support the emergence of transformative non-ordinary states of consciousness.</blockquote></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Holotropic Breathwork</h1></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Holotropic Breathwork is a guided breathing practice that supports emotional release, self-awareness, and personal growth. It can complement psychotherapy and psychedelic therapy integration.</h2></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><br>I run workshops and one-on-one sessions in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick\">Melbourne</a> and the <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne\">Surf Coast</a>, creating a safe space for self-exploration, emotional release, and personal growth.</p>\n<p>Holotropic Breathwork was developed by Stanislav and Christina Grof in order to facilitate the healing potential of non-ordinary states of consciousness - primarily via the manipulation of the breath.</p>\n<p>Given the right setting, it is possible to powerfully alter your normal waking consciousness and allow yourself to become immersed within a rich and diverse inner world of experience. The processing of this experience helps the breather to strengthen self awareness, process trauma and other unresolved life experiences and build a dialogue between the waking consciousness and what Stan Grof coined the Inner Healer (Inner Healing Mechanism).</p>\n<p>It is this inner healer that helps to catalyse our movement towards wholeness (the literal meaning of the word Holotropic), by providing inner experiences that can thematically represent important psychological, spiritual, emotional and physical issues that may be present within us. When these elements are processed, we allow for the possibility of transformation of our fears, anxieties and other tensions. The resolution of these tensions help to ground us in our relationship with ourselves, people important to us and the world around us.</p>\n<p>Each session uses guided breathing, music, and a safe container to help you explore inner experiences, process unresolved emotions, and deepen self-awareness. Whether in a group workshop or one-on-one, sessions are tailored to your needs and paced to support personal insight and integration.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo has-section-width-uk-container row-columns-2-3_1-3 padding-large\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n             <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>My Holotropic Breathwork experience</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork has been a fundamental influence on how I&nbsp;﻿approach all aspects of my life and indeed since the late 1990\'s it has been the primary tool I&nbsp;﻿have used in order to gain greater insight into my life.</p>\n<p>﻿My work with Alf Foote was foundational in terms of demonstrating the transformative potential of the breath. And from 2006 to 2013 my training to become a Holotropic Breathwork facilitator via <a href=\"http://holotropic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GTT</a>&nbsp;further grounded my understanding of the healing power of non-ordinary states of consciousness.</p>\n<p>﻿Since 2013 I&nbsp;﻿have been running Holotropic Breathwork Workshops in Melbourne with <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/practitioners/ruth-langford\" target=\"_blank\">Ruth Langford</a> and others and I&nbsp;﻿am also a senior staff member of the official <a href=\"https://www.holotropic.com\">Grof Transpersonal Training</a> for Holotropic Breathwork..</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What is Holotropic Breathwork?</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork is conducted in a very specific set and setting. On the outside Holotropic Breathwork may look like many other forms of breathwork however there are some key differences.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>The Holotropic Breathwork Technique is deceptively simple ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork is a low-tech breathing technique and in fact (paradoxically) how you breathe is perhaps the least important element in a Holotropic Breathwork session. The key instruction for breathing Holotropically is to \"Breathe a little bit faster and a little bit deeper - ensuring that your breathing is continuous and without pause\".</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Holotropic Breathwork is always done with a sitter ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Any Holotropic Breathwork is done with at least one sitter and ideally with a facilitator. Holotropic Breathwork is a relational breathwork modality and at it\'s core is the understanding that we heal through relationship with the other. The sitter is a crucial element in the Holotropic container as they ensure that the process can unfold in a safe and undisturbed way, they can offer support to the breather if it\'s required and can help to ensure that the breathwork process itself is completed as much as possible in that moment. With any type of non-ordinary state work, completing the process will help to avoid any potential for fragmentation after the session has ended.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Holotropic Breathwork is non-directive ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>All Holotropic Breathwork sessions are conducted knowing that the breather is the expert in their process. In that the breathers Inner Healer knows how to provide an experience that will best allow for the opening and resolution of material. This means that the role of the facilitator is simply to help provide a container that is wide enough and deep&nbsp;enough to hold the experience. Importantly, Meaning making is not a part of the facilitators role in Holotropic Breathwork. Moreover their primarily role is that of supporting the breather and helping the process to unfold in a way that facilitates the dialogue between the breather and the inner healer.</p>\n<p>﻿Another key element of the non-directive nature of the process is that there is no hierarchy of experience. By this I&nbsp;﻿mean that grand, transcendent light filled experiences are just as important as difficult, emotional and sometimes painful experiences. The key part of any experience is the successful completion of the process regardless of the material.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Music is an important part of Holotropic Breathwork session ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>The music is a key element of a Holotropic Breathwork session as it helps to hold the experience of the breather. It is played at a high volume so it can be used as a support for the breathers process. The arc of a breathwork set is like a wave:﻿﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><ul><li>The initial phase is a build up -&nbsp;&nbsp;intense, rhythmic music designed to entrain the brain</li><li>The second phase contains more emotional / peak music aimed at facilitating breakthrough and release</li><li>The last phase is a gentle period of prayerful and meditation music.</li></ul></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>A Holotropic Breathwork session typically runs for 2.5 to 3 hours.</p>\n<p>﻿You can find a curated list of music used in Holotropic Breathwork sessions on my website <a href=\"http://www.musicforbreathwork.com\" target=\"_blank\">Music for Breathwork</a>.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/silas-baisch-OCzvgBqCJKY-unsplash_ktsdyk\" data-image=\"gdwc0edytmgd\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                                                                                            </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo uk-dark\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3><b>﻿One on One Breathwork Sessions</b></h3>\n<p>In some cases we may be able to do shorter one on one holotropic inspired breathwork. This form of breathwork differs slightly from what you might experience in a workshop setting however it is suitable as a form of release /exploration in conjunction with ongoing psychotherapeutic support.</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"uk-margin-remove\"></figure>\n<h2><b>What is the process for doing breathwork in a one on one setting?</b></h2>\n<p>One on one breathwork unfolds in a series of 3 steps:</p>\n<h3><b>Step 1</b>&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>Meet for a one hour psychotherapy session where we can chat about Breathwork and you can share some of your story about what. brings you to breathwork. <a href=\"http://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\">Book your first session</a>.</p>\n<h3><b>Step 2</b>&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>The breathwork session itself is a 3 hour session which includes a 2 hour breathwork process as well as a pre-chat and some integration work after the session.</p>\n<h3><b>Step 3</b>&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>A follow up one hour integration session where we can work further to deepen the&nbsp;&nbsp;insight and awareness gathered during the breathwork session. Integration is an important part of any non-ordinary state work - it\'s a process that supports the bringing of the wisdom gleaned in the session into your relationship and every day life.</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"uk-margin-remove\"></figure>\n<h2><b>What are the differences working one on one vs working in a workshop setting?</b></h2>\n<ul><li>Breathwork in the one on one format is typically shorter -2 hours, whereas workshop sessions go for 2.5 to 3 hours each In a workshop setting you also have the experience of sitting for another person - this is often a powerful experience by itself.&nbsp;</li><li>In a workshop there is dedicated time and space to integrate the session via sitting in circle with others as well as dedicated time for mandala drawing and other art practice. Whereas in the one on one format there is limited time to do this integration work. One on one sessions are ideal for those who are not comfortable with doing this kind of work in a group setting.&nbsp;</li><li>One on one sessions can be used as a tool to work with ongoing material being worked on in your psychotherapy sessions with myself or other practitioners.</li><li>Please note that&nbsp;One on one sessions are not technically considered to be Holotropic Breathwork, but are Holotropic inspired. For a breathwork session to be considered Holotropic the session needs to run for at least&nbsp;2.5 hours and&nbsp;the breather also has an opportunity to sit for another breather.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"uk-margin-remove\"></figure>\n<h2><b>Pricing Structure</b></h2>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Introductory session: $160 (50 minutes)</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Breathwork Session: $395 (3 hours)</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Integration Session: $160 (50 minutes)</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr class=\"uk-margin-remove\"></figure>\n<h2><b>Cancellation Fee:</b></h2>\n<p><b></b>Introductory and integration sessions have a standard $160 cancellation fee within 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Breathwork sessions have a $200 cancellation fee within 72 hours of the session.</p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/javier-esteban-JAsWBt-IOj8-unsplash_xhsrqh\" data-image=\"kxo1qcexzy6s\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', 'https://', 'meagan-carsience-TpG2TBiclik-unsplash_gy44ix_exacii', 1314, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork was developed by Stanislav and Christina Grof in order to facilitate the healing potential of non-ordinary states of consciousness - primarily via the manipulation of the breath.\n﻿Given the right setting, it is possible to powerfully alter your normal waking consciousness and allow yourself to become immersed within a rich and diverse inner world of experience. The processing of this experience helps the breather to strengthen self awareness, process trauma and other unresolved life experiences and build a dialogue between the waking consciousness and what Stan Grof coined the Inner Healer (Inner Healing Mechanism).\n\n﻿It is this inner healer that helps to catalyse our movement towards wholeness (the literal meaning of the word Holotropic), by providing inner experiences that can thematically represent important psychological, spiritual, emotional and physical issues that may be present within us. When these elements are processed, we allow for the possibility of transformation of our fears, anxieties and other tensions. The resolution of these tensions help to ground us in our relationship with ourselves, people important to us and the world around us.', 'One on one Holotropic Breathwork Sessions', NULL, 'Explore Holotropic Breathwork, a powerful technique by Stanislav and Christina Grof. Enhance self-awareness, process unresolved experiences, and engage with your Inner Healer for holistic transformation.', '2025-07-01 02:11:24', '2026-04-02 00:10:59', 48, NULL, 6, NULL, 0, 6, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2931, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Mens Groups', 'experiential-mens-groups', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3 padding-small has-section-width-uk-container-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_dzpjbc_l83k0a\" data-image=\"x17x71dcjnve\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                                                                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/mens-groups/2026-experiential-mens-group\" class=\"w-full uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">2026 FIRST SEMESTER COHORT NOW OPEN</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 60px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px;\">Deep listening circles aimed at providing a space for men to develop intimacy and greater relational awareness.</blockquote></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                            <div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\" style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Experiential Men\'s Groups</h1></div></div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>It\'s not an understatement to suggest that the last 20 years has seen a huge change in awareness of the role of Men in society.&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>﻿<a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/mens-groups/2026-experiential-mens-group\">Bookings are now open for the 2026 First Semester cohort</a></p>\n<p>Men are often being called to extend and deepen the way they are in the world, and explore ways to embody what might be called a more healthy masculinity. These groups have been created to provide a safe and supportive container for this exploration.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>What are they and when are they held?</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Series of groups are held throughout the year around specific topics such as The Mature&nbsp;Masculine Archetypes, The Hero\'s Journey, The Family System, Work and more. They are experiential sessions that may include meditation, music, movies, ritual and deep listening, that are aimed at providing an opportunity for like minded men to meet and share life experience in a non-judgemental forum.</p>\n<p>Each session follows the following format.</p>\n<ul><li>Introduction of the topic﻿<br></li><li>Reflective process exploring the topic - through music, movie or meditation</li><li>Some small group sharing</li><li>Larger group discussion of each participants life experience</li><li>Then a more general discussion on the topic before the close.﻿</li></ul></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block new-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Participants are encouraged to share from their personal experience and to try and avoid theory and philosophy as a way of engaging in the topic. When we are able to stay as close to our experience as possible it opens up the possibility of creating more intimate relationships around us.﻿﻿</p>\n<p>It is important to note that&nbsp;﻿these sessions are also not therapy groups. The circle\'s are held in a deeply democratic fashion&nbsp;with the belief that each participant has an important contribution to make in the group. Each contribution is respected and listened to in a way that ensures the group remains open to a diverse range of experiences.﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', 'https://', 'cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_dzpjbc_l83k0a', 1314, 1, 'It\'s not an understatement to suggest that the last 20 years has seen a huge change in awareness of the role of Men in society. Men are often being called to extend and deepen the way they are in the world, and explore ways to embody what might be called a more healthy masculinity. These groups have been created to provide a safe and supportive container for this exploration.', 'Experiential Men\'s Groups | Deep Listening Circles &amp; Workshops', NULL, 'Join our experiential men\'s groups for deep listening circles and workshops. Develop greater relational awareness and explore healthy masculinity in a safe, supportive space. Register your interest now.', '2025-07-01 02:11:27', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 48, NULL, 7, NULL, 0, 7, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2932, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Retrievals and dispatches', 'retrievals-and-dispatches', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-middle with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3 padding-none has-section-width-uk-container-large\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1042/wolf-feather-mythic_lp5s0e\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary w-full\">﻿BOOK A SESSION</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin: 60px 0px 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 60px 0px 0px;\">When we find ourselves in the depths of pain, it can be easy for our systems to feel overwhelmed. In these moments, of being broken open, it can seem as though we’ve lost connection to who we truly are. We may feel untethered, abandoned, and as if a vital part of ourselves is missing.</blockquote></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>Dispatching, retrieving &amp; reconnecting</h1></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>In profound places of pain and distress, our psyche and soul sometimes draw in external forces as a means of support. These external influences are&nbsp;what Internal Family Systems refers to as \"Unattached Burdens\" or Shaman might call attachments.&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>Put simply an Unattached Burden is an element within the system that does not originate from within the system. For example, on one end of the spectrum this may be something as simple as absorbing the emotion (e.g. anger) from those around us to help us to feel empowered. At the other end of the spectrum this may be akin to what shamanic cultures call spirit possession, where more complex constellations of personas are absorbed into the system in an attempt to make it whole. ﻿﻿</p>\n<p>In response to grief, trauma, and loss these external forces may offer a sense of relief or stability in the moment. However, over time, these burden can drain our systems and obscure our path back to wholeness.</p>\n<p>Through a compassionate and affirming process of reconnection—to self, soul, spirit, and inner wholeness—it becomes possible to release these burdens. By doing so, we reclaim our inner wisdom and rediscover the strength and clarity that has always resided within us.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Retrieving</h2>\n<p>Sometimes, instead of drawing external energies into the system for support, our psyche&nbsp;chooses another path: exiling feelings that are too overwhelming to process. This creates fierce boundaries and protections around the painful parts of ourselves. While these strategies may offer temporary stability, they often leave the system operating with reduced energy, a sense of unnamed and unknown loss, and, in some cases, can be experienced as disassociation.</p>\n<p>﻿To work with these conditions, it is essential to approach these protective mechanisms with deep respect, honouring the extraordinary work they’ve done to preserve the system’s sense of safety and equilibrium. Healing begins by gently engaging with the protective parts of the psyche, understanding their fears, and updating their awareness of the inner system’s current state.</p>\n<p>﻿These protectors are often frozen in time, locked at the moment of their creation. The process of healing involves “unfreezing” these protections, reclaiming the exiled emotions they guard, and reintegrating them into the system. This careful and compassionate retrieval brings the system back into balance, restoring vitality, connection, and wholeness.﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Reconnecting</h2>\n<p>A central aspect of any healing journey involves the reintegration of the parts of ourselves that were exiled and the repair of any vulnerabilities that allowed external influences to take root within the system. This process is about restoring balance, wholeness, and integrity to the psyche.In Holotropic Breathwork, this transformative process is guided by what we call \"The Inner Healer.\"</p>\n<p> ﻿In Internal Family Systems, it is referred to as \"the capital-S Self,\" and others may recognize it as the soul or core essence. Regardless of the terminology, the principle remains the same: every individual possesses an inherent capacity to heal.</p>\n<p> ﻿This capacity emerges naturally when we cultivate awareness and trust in our innate potential for transformation.By tapping into this inner source of wisdom and healing, we awaken the ability to utilize and amplify our own internal resources. This not only fosters deep restoration and integration but also creates profound strength and resilience within our systems, allowing us to navigate life with greater depth, clarity, and empowerment.</p>\n<p></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What do these sessions look like?</h2>\n<p>Dispatching, retrieving, and reconnecting involve delving into our inner landscape and cultivating a deeper understanding of its underlying dynamics. This is accomplished by accessing light trance states and non-ordinary states of consciousness, allowing us to tap into our innate healing potential. These states are facilitated through a blend of conscious breathing, somatic awareness, guided visualization, and inner dialogue.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Sessions draw significant inspiration from the Internal Family Systems (IFS) model, a parts-based approach to psychotherapy that emphasizes understanding and integrating the various \"parts\" of the psyche. At times, these sessions may also take on a shamanic quality, blending therapeutic principles with a deeper, more spiritual exploration of the self.</p>\n<p>﻿Participants often experience deep and embodied feelings of support and connection and often report feeling relief particularly after the release of unattached burdens.</p>\n<p>﻿Sessions are 80 minutes long and cost $240.</p>\n<p></p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', 'https://', 'wolf-medicine_wy2wzj', 1314, 1, 'When we find ourselves in the depths of pain, it can be easy for our systems to feel overwhelmed. In these moments, of being broken open, it can seem as though we’ve lost connection to who we truly are. We may feel untethered, abandoned, and as if a vital part of ourselves is missing.', 'Reconnecting and Rediscovering Your Inner Strength', NULL, 'Explore a compassionate process of reconnecting to self, spirit, and inner wholeness. Release burdens and reclaim inner wisdom to rediscover your strength and clarity.', '2025-07-01 02:11:30', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 48, NULL, 8, NULL, 0, 8, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2933, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Contact', 'contact', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-40 uk-flex-middle padding-large uk-dark has-section-width-uk-container row-columns-1-4_3-4\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>If you’d like to book a session, ask a question, or simply explore whether therapy here feels like the right fit, you’re welcome to get in touch at any time. You can call me directly on <b>0416277063</b>&nbsp;for a quick conversation, or use the <strong>contact form on this page</strong> to send a message at your convenience.&nbsp;</p><p>I’ll usually get back to you within one business day. Whether it’s to book a full session, arrange an introductory chat, or clarify anything before starting, I’m here to help make the process as simple and supportive as possible.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Make Contact</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-mode=\"readonly\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n                                    <span data-id=\"5\" data-type=\"Contact\" data-source=\"\" data-parent=\"0\" data-display=\"default\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-layout=\"default\">[widget:5|Contact]</span>\n                                </div></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-auto uk-dark padding-large uk-flex-top overlay-none with-redo row-columns-1-4_3-4\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Finding Us</h2></div>\n                        </div>\n                                            </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p>\n<p>Wild Heart Psychotherapy is located at <strong>503 Sydney Road, Brunswick</strong>, in the heart of Melbourne’s inner north. You’ll find us near the corner of Sydney Road and Blyth Street, surrounded by cafes, small shops, and the vibrant energy that makes Brunswick such a welcoming place.</p>\n<p>Getting here is easy. If you’re coming by tram, the <strong>Route 19 tram stops almost directly outside the building at Stop 22 (Blyth St/Sydney Rd)</strong>. For those travelling by train, it’s a short walk from <strong>Anstey Station</strong> on the Upfield line. Several bus routes also run along Blyth Street and nearby Nicholson Street, making public transport a convenient option.</p>\n<p>If you’re driving, there is usually <strong>1-2 hour street parking available along Sydney Road</strong>, as well as longer-term parking options in nearby residential streets – just be sure to check the signs for time limits.</p>\n<p>When you arrive, look for <strong>503 Sydney Road</strong>. You’ll find clear signage for Wild Heart Psychotherapy inside. Please aim to arrive at your scheduled time, as waiting areas are limited. If you have any questions about accessibility, parking, or finding the entrance, feel free to get in touch before your session. I look forward to welcoming you here.</p>\n<p></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-mode=\"readonly\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n                                    <span data-id=\"6\" data-type=\"Map\" data-source=\"Clinic Address\" data-parent=\"0\" data-display=\"default\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-layout=\"default\">[widget:6|Map|Clinic Address]</span>\n                                </div></div>\n                        </div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2025-07-02 02:54:12', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'therapy_ydfwfv', 1314, 1, '', 'Contact and Location - Wild Heart Psychotherapy, Brunswick', NULL, 'Get in touch to book a session or ask a question at Wild Heart Psychotherapy. Conveniently located in Brunswick, Melbourne, with easy access by tram, train and bus.', '2025-07-02 02:54:28', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 0, NULL, 9, NULL, 0, 11, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2934, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Book an introductory chat', 'book-an-introductory-chat', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-50 uk-flex-middle with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large row-columns-1-1\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Book a 20 minute introductory chat</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>If you aren\'t quite ready to <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\">book a full session</a> or you have some questions about how I work&nbsp;you book an introductory chat below.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://app.acuityscheduling.com/schedule.php?owner=34409969&amp;calendarID=13317373&amp;ref=embedded_csp\" title=\"Schedule Appointment\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"payment\"></iframe></figure></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'therapy_ydfwfv', 1314, 1, '', 'Book a 20-minute Introductory Chat - Get Your Queries Resolved', NULL, 'Don\'t rush into a full session. Book a 20-minute introductory chat with us to ask your questions and understand our work process better.', '2025-07-03 07:01:29', '2026-01-05 02:23:17', 3, NULL, 10, NULL, 0, 15, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2935, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Finding psychotherapy in Brunswick', 'finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 row-columns-1-3 padding-none has-section-width-uk-container\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751242021/1314/norway_k1dqti.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"4tbfu72way1w\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary w-full\">﻿BOOK A SESSION</a></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><section>\n  <div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n    <p class=\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6\">Wild Heart Psychotherapy in&nbsp;﻿Brunswick</p>\n\n    <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-8\">\n      Wild Heart Psychotherapy is now located at <strong>503 Sydney Road, Brunswick</strong>, in the heart of Melbourne’s inner north. This vibrant and accessible location is ideal for anyone seeking psychotherapy, counselling, or inner exploration in a warm and welcoming space.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-8\">I also now offer <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne\">counselling sessions in Lorne, Surf Coast Vic</a>.</p>\n\n    <div class=\"mb-8\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Our New Location</h2>\n      <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Address:</strong><br>503 Sydney Road<br>Brunswick VIC 3056</p>\n\n      <h3 class=\"text-xl font-medium text-gray-700 mt-4 mb-2\">Key Features:</h3>\n      <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2\">\n        <li><strong>Central Brunswick location:</strong> Near the corner of Sydney Road and Blyth Street, surrounded by local cafes, shops, and community services.</li>\n        <li><strong>Public transport accessibility:</strong>\n          <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-6\">\n            <li><strong>Tram:</strong> Route 19 tram stops directly outside (Stop 22 – Blyth St/Sydney Rd).</li>\n            <li><strong>Train:</strong> Short walk from Anstey Station on the Upfield line.</li>\n            <li><strong>Bus:</strong> Routes along Blyth Street and nearby Nicholson Street.</li>\n          </ul>\n        </li>\n        <li><strong>Parking:</strong>\n          <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-6\">\n            <li>Limited 1-2 hour street parking on Sydney Road and surrounds.</li>\n            <li>Longer parking options in residential side streets (check signage).</li>\n          </ul>\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"mb-8\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">About the Space</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-2\">The practice room is designed to feel calm, grounded, and welcoming. It features:</p>\n      <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2\">\n        <li>Comfortable seating for individual or couples therapy</li>\n        <li>Warm natural lighting</li>\n        <li>Climate control for all seasons</li>\n        <li>A peaceful atmosphere amidst the lively Brunswick surroundings</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"mb-8\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Who This Space Serves</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-2\">Wild Heart Psychotherapy offers:</p>\n      <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2\">\n        <li><strong>Individual psychotherapy and counselling</strong> for adults seeking support with anxiety, depression, grief, life transitions, self-exploration, or integration of expanded state experiences.</li>\n        <li><strong>Holotropic Breathwork integration sessions</strong> to support breathwork or psychedelic therapy journeys with grounded psychological and somatic integration.</li>\n        <li><strong>Creative and somatic therapy approaches</strong> drawing on Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal Psychology frameworks.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"mb-8\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Why Brunswick?</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-gray-700\">Brunswick is a diverse, culturally rich area known for its community-minded feel and accessibility. Being located here makes it easier for people from <strong>Coburg, Carlton, Northcote, Thornbury, Fitzroy, and the Melbourne CBD</strong> to attend sessions without the stress of long commutes.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Visiting Wild Heart Psychotherapy</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-2\">When you arrive:</p>\n      <ol class=\"list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2\">\n        <li>Look for the <strong>503 Sydney Road</strong> entrance, near Blyth Street.</li>\n        <li>You’ll find clear signage for Wild Heart Psychotherapy inside the building.</li>\n        <li>Please arrive at your scheduled time, as the waiting area is limited.</li>\n      </ol>\n      <p class=\"text-gray-700 mt-4\">If you have any questions about getting to the practice, parking, or accessibility needs, feel free to get in touch before your appointment.</p>\n    </div>\n\n   \n  </div>\n</section></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2025-07-03 07:13:46', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'wolf-medicine_wy2wzj', 1314, 1, '', 'Wild Heart Psychotherapy in Brunswick, Melbourne', NULL, 'Wild Heart Psychotherapy in Brunswick offers individual and couples therapy, holotropic breathwork sessions, and creative therapy approaches in a calm and welcoming space. Easy access via public transport and local parking.', '2025-07-03 07:14:08', '2026-01-13 21:44:35', 0, NULL, 11, NULL, 0, 10, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2976, 1042, 857, 1042, 1042, 1, 'Couples Breathwork Therapy Sessions', 'couples-breathwork-therapy-sessions', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-light padding-large uk-flex-bottom height-600px\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_1200/1042/meagan-carsience-TpG2TBiclik-unsplash_gkl42k_l9zed5_pu3ce5&quot;);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m content-block\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Holotropic Breathwork for Couples</h1>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\">\n                        Combining Holotropic Breathwork with ongoing couples work to expand and deepen connection, communication and understanding</h2></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: block; opacity: 0.2; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n        </div></div>\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large uk-flex-middle with-redo\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2 content-block\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Couples therapy is a powerful tool that helps couples improve their relationship by providing them with the tools and skills they need to communicate effectively, resolve conflicts, and build a stronger bond. However, for couples who are looking for a more transformative and holistic approach to therapy, Holotropic Breathwork is an exciting option to consider.</h3>\n<p>Holotropic Breathwork is a form of therapy that combines deep breathing techniques, music, and bodywork to access the deeper parts of the psyche. It was developed by Stanislav Grof, a Czech psychiatrist who spent decades researching non-ordinary states of consciousness, and it is based on the idea that the human psyche has the innate ability to heal itself.</p>\n<p>When combined with couples therapy, Holotropic Breathwork can help couples access deeper levels of awareness and understanding, leading to greater self-awareness and improved communication. Here are some of the ways that couples therapy combined with Holotropic Breathwork can benefit your relationship:</p>\n<h4><b>1. Increased emotional intimacy&nbsp;</b></h4>\n<p><b></b>Holotropic Breathwork can help couples connect on a deeper emotional level, allowing them to access feelings and emotions that may be difficult to articulate. By engaging in this practice together, couples can create a safe and supportive environment where they can explore their feelings and connect with each other in a more meaningful way.</p>\n<h4><b>2. Greater self-awareness&nbsp;</b></h4>\n<p><b></b>Through Holotropic Breathwork, couples can gain a greater understanding of their own thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. This increased self-awareness can help them identify patterns in their relationship that may be holding them back and make the necessary changes to improve their relationship.</p>\n<h4><b>3. Improved communication</b>&nbsp;</h4>\n<p>Holotropic Breathwork can help couples improve their communication skills by providing them with a deeper understanding of their own emotions and needs. This increased awareness can lead to more open and honest communication, which can strengthen the bond between partners and reduce conflict.</p>\n<h4><b>4. Deeper empathy</b>&nbsp;</h4>\n<p>By experiencing non-ordinary states of consciousness together, couples can develop a greater sense of empathy for each other. This can help them understand each other\'s perspectives and feelings on a deeper level, leading to a more compassionate and supportive relationship.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2 content-block uk-text-center\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/daniel-j-schwarz-YtY724tdl7Y-unsplash_q9d47g\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n             <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/Therapy-couch_blnacf\" data-image=\"gdwc0edytmgd\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What is involved with&nbsp;Holotropic Breathwork for couples therapy?</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork for couples therapy includes 3 sessions:</p>\n<h4><b>﻿Session 1</b> - Introduction and preparation (50 Minutes)</h4>\n<p>﻿During the integration and preparation session we will discuss the various themes that are emerging in the relationship and how they are impacting the relationship. We will also discuss the theory and practice of Holotropic Breathwork and how breathwork may support the working through of those themes.</p>\n<h4>﻿<b>﻿Session 2</b> - The breathwork session day. (10am to 4:30pm).</h4>\n<p>﻿This is a whole day of breathwork where you will take part in two breathwork sessions. Each breathwork session will run for 2.5 hours and you will have an opportunity to sit for your partner while they breathe and they will sit for you while you breathe. The process of sitting in breathwork is often described as being just as powerful as the breathwork process itself.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿There will be an opportunity to integration work on the day after each session as well as time for lunch.</p>\n<h4><b>﻿Session 3&nbsp;</b>﻿- Integration (50 Minutes)<br></h4>\n<p>The ﻿integration phase for any non-ordinary states of awareness work is crucial as it helps us to make sense of the experience and too help us to understand how we might be able to bring the wisdom and insight from the experience into our daily lives and importantly into our relationships.</p>\n<p>﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3><b>Who is this suited for?</b></h3>\n<p>﻿While breathwork may well be a powerful tool for developing self awareness it is not always the right choice for some individuals. Ideally couples who attend this couples breathwork work are already in some form of couples or individual counselling, have a degree of communication skills within the relationship.</p>\n<p>﻿A key factor of suitability for couples doing this work is that there are no occurrences of domestic violence nor the threat of such violence. For non-ordinary state work to be truly supportive&nbsp;the container the work is performed in must have some capacity for each party to take ownership of their experience and that there be limited projection onto the other of that experience. If you are interested in doing this work but are not sure if this is right for you, you may like to book a <a href=\"http://@page/page-26\">free 15 minute introductory phone</a> call where we can discuss those concerns.</p>\n<h3><b>﻿Pricing Structure</b><br></h3>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">The cost of the&nbsp;whole package including introduction, session and integration is $1200.</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\"><a href=\"http://@page/page-5\">﻿Bookings can be made for the first introductory session via my appointments page</a>.</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿At the end of that session we will book in a time to complete the rest of the sessions.</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿</p>\n<h3 data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿<b>﻿Cancellation Fee:</b></h3>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\"><b></b>﻿Introductory and integration sessions have a standard $160 cancellation fee within 24 hours.﻿﻿﻿</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿Breathwork sessions have a $200 cancellation fee within 72 hours of the session.</p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/DALL_E_2023-05-30_09.49.32_-_sacred_nature_digital_art_au5ngv\" data-image=\"kxo1qcexzy6s\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo uk-light\" style=\"background-color: rgb(55, 71, 79);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>My Holotropic Breathwork experience</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork has been a fundamental influence on how I&nbsp;﻿approach all aspects of my life and indeed since the late 1990\'s it has been the primary tool I&nbsp;﻿have used in order to gain greater insight into my life.</p>\n<p>﻿My work with Alf Foote was foundational in terms of demonstrating the transformative potential of the breath. And from 2006 to 2013 my training to become a Holotropic Breathwork facilitator via <a href=\"http://holotropic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GTT</a>&nbsp;further grounded my understanding of the healing power of non-ordinary states of consciousness.</p>\n<p>﻿Since 2013 I&nbsp;﻿have been running Holotropic Breathwork Workshops in Melbourne with <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/practitioners/ruth-langford\" target=\"_blank\">Ruth Langford</a> and others and have also been on staff as a part of the <a href=\"https://holotropic.com.au/training\" target=\"_blank\">Grof Transpersonal Training programs</a> in Australia.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Holotropic Breathwork is held in workshops and smallgroups</h4></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>For a schedule of upcoming workshops and groups please visit the <a href=\"http://melbournebreathwork.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Melbourne Breathwork website</a>.&nbsp; Workshops will re-commence in February 2021.﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/workshops\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">VIEW UPCOMING EVENTS</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/IMG_1025_v3lm0h\" data-image=\"riefmxhq4izs\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'daniel-j-schwarz-YtY724tdl7Y-unsplash_q9d47g', 1042, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork for Couples\nCombining Holotropic Breathwork with ongoing couples work to expand and deepen connection, communication and understanding', 'Holotropic Breathwork: Transformative Therapy for Couples', NULL, 'Explore Holotropic Breathwork, a holistic therapy that enhances communication and deepens connection in relationships. Meld breathwork with couples therapy for increased emotional intimacy and self-awareness.', '2025-07-04 07:46:54', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 3, NULL, 16, NULL, 1, 16, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2985, 1042, 857, 1042, 1042, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork Bookings', 'holotropic-breathworl-appointments', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-light padding-large uk-flex-bottom overlay-dark with-redo height-600px\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_1200/1042/silas-baisch-OCzvgBqCJKY-unsplash_ktsdyk&quot;);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-small\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\" style=\"\">\n                        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\" style=\"\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>﻿Book One on One Holotropic&nbsp;</h1>\n<h1>inspired&nbsp;Breathwork Sessions</h1></div>\n</div>                                            </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-40 uk-flex-middle padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-1\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-small\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\" style=\"\">\n                                                                        \n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\" style=\"\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What is involved in a one on one&nbsp;Breathwork&nbsp;session?</h2>\n<h4>In some cases we may be able to do shorter one on one holotropic inspired breathwork. This form of breathwork differs slightly from what you might experience in a <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com\" target=\"_blank\">workshop setting</a> however it is suitable as a form of release /exploration in conjunction with ongoing psychotherapeutic support.<br></h4>\n<p><b>What are the differences working one on one vs working in a workshop setting?</b></p>\n<ul><li>Breathwork in the one on one format is typically shorter - from 40 minutes to 2 hours, whereas workshop sessions go for 2.5 to 3 hours</li><li>In a workshop setting you also have the experience of sitting for another person - this is often a powerful experience by itself.</li><li>In a workshop there is dedicated time and space to integrate the session via sitting in circle with others as well as dedicated time for mandala drawing and other art practice. Whereas in the one on one format there is limited time to do this integration work.</li><li>One on one sessions are ideal for those who are not comfortable with doing this kind of work in a group setting.</li><li>One on one sessions can be used as a tool to work with ongoing material being worked on in your psychotherapy sessions with myself or other practitioners.</li></ul>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure>\n<h2><b>Pricing Structure &amp;&nbsp;Session Booking Process</b></h2>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Introductory session: $140 (50 Minute)</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Breathwork Session: $345 (2.5 -&nbsp;3 hours)</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Integration&nbsp;Session: $140 (50 Minutes)</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\"></p>\n<p><b>Please note:</b></p>\n<p>Before requesting a booking below please ensure that you have already had an introductory session which can be <a href=\"http://@page/page-5\">booked here</a>.</p>\n<p>If you have already attended a Melbourne Breathwork Workshop please arrange a time to have a catch up on the phone before booking a one on one breathwork session.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Initial introductory session. can be booked below:</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;﻿</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><iframe src=\"https://app.squarespacescheduling.com/schedule.php?owner=21951962&amp;owner=21951962&amp;appointmentType=33337327\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></figure>\n<p></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-dark overlay-none with-redo padding-none height-300px uk-flex-top has-section-width-uk-container-expand\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-expand\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-mode=\"readonly\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\" data-active=\"0\">\n                                    <span data-id=\"34\" data-type=\"Map\" data-source=\"Clinic Address\" data-parent=\"0\" data-display=\"default\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\">[widget:34|Map|Clinic Address]</span>\n                                </div></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'sean-brown-2384_1_c8n54i', 0, 1, 'In some cases we may be able to do shorter one on one holotropic inspired breathwork. This form of breathwork differs slightly from what you might experience in a workshop setting however it is suitable as a form of release /exploration in conjunction with ongoing psychotherapeutic support.', 'Holotropic Breathwork One-on-One Sessions | Book Now', NULL, 'Explore personalized Holotropic Breathwork sessions. Ideal for those seeking a private setting. Suitable for ongoing therapeutic support. Introductory, Breathwork, and Integration sessions available.', '2025-07-04 07:46:54', '2026-01-05 00:10:29', 0, NULL, 25, NULL, 1, 19, NULL, 0, NULL),
	(2991, 1042, 857, 1042, 1042, 1, 'Men\'s Groups', 'mens-groups', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-light padding-large uk-flex-bottom bg-position-bottom height-600px overlay-dark\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_1200/1042/cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_dzpjbc&quot;);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m content-block\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\" style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">\n                        Men\'s Circles and Groups</h1>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\" style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">\n                        Deep listening circles aimed at providing a container for men</h2>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\" style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">to develop intimacy and greater relational awareness.</h2></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>It\'s not an understatement to suggest that the last 20 years has seen a huge change in awareness of the role of Men in society. Men are often being called to extend and deepen the way they are in the world, and explore ways to embody what might be called a more healthy masculinity. These groups have been created to provide a safe and supportive container for this exploration.</h4></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                                                <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>What are they and when are they held?</h3></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Series of groups are held throughout the year around specific topics such as The Mature&nbsp;Masculine Archetypes, The Hero\'s Journey, The Family System, Work and more. They are experiential sessions that may include meditation, music, movies, ritual and deep listening, that are aimed at providing an opportunity for like minded men to meet and share life experience in a non-judgemental forum.</p>\n<p>Each session follows the following format.</p>\n<ul><li>Introduction of the topic﻿<br></li><li>Reflective process exploring the topic - through music, movie or meditation</li><li>Some small group sharing</li><li>Larger group discussion of each participants life experience</li><li>Then a more general discussion on the topic before the close.</li></ul>\n<p>Participants are encouraged to share from their personal experience and to try and avoid theory and philosophy as a way of engaging in the topic. When we are able to stay as close to our experience as possible it opens up the possibility of creating more intimate relationships around us.</p>\n<p>It is important to note that&nbsp;﻿these sessions are also not therapy groups. The circle\'s are held in a deeply democratic fashion&nbsp;with the belief that each participant has an important contribution to make in the group. Each contribution is respected and listened to in a way that ensures the group remains open to a diverse range of experiences.﻿﻿<br>﻿﻿﻿<br></p></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/jeremy-bishop-7JPerNWjEAE-unsplash_zftuhh\" data-image=\"x17x71dcjnve\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-auto uk-flex-top padding-large with-redo uk-dark has-section-width-uk-container\" style=\"background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>Upcoming workshops</b></h2></div>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"24\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"List\" data-source=\"Events\">[widget:24|List|Events]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_ndpn2c', 1042, 1, 'Experiential listening circles crafted to open ways for men to connect and create deeper connections. Workshops are held periodically throughout the year, with each series organised around a diverse range of topics.', 'Men\'s Circles: Enhancing Healthy Masculinity & Relational Awareness', NULL, 'Join our Men\'s Circles and Groups to deepen your understanding of healthy masculinity. Participate in experiential sessions on diverse topics, fostering intimacy and relational awareness in a non-judgmental environment.', '2025-07-04 07:46:54', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 3, NULL, 31, NULL, 1, 17, NULL, 0, ''),
	(2996, 1042, 857, 1042, 1042, 1, 'Psychedelic Integration', 'psychedelic-integration', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-light padding-large uk-flex-bottom height-600px overlay-dark bg-position-center\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_1200/1042/fly-d-xcG3Yg6iCQg-unsplash_slfqyx&quot;);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m content-block\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Psychedelic Integration</h1>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\">\n                        Integrating non-ordinary states of consciousness</h2></div></div></div></div></div></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\">\n        </div></div>\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large uk-flex-middle with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>It\'s no secret that psychedelics have been undergoing a resurgence in popular culture over the last decade. New science has been revealing what psychonauts through the ages of known - that psychedelic and non-ordinary states have an enormous power to change, shape and re-frame our lives. However the question remains - what do we do with the experience?</h3></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3><b>What are the components of a psychedelic session?</b><br></h3>\n<p>Any experience involving&nbsp;non-ordinary state of consciousness can be broken into 3 parts:</p>\n<ol><li>Preparation</li><li>﻿Session</li><li>﻿﻿integration</li></ol>\n<p>﻿Without the proper attention to any of these three parts there is a much greater potential for fragmentation, de-stabilisation or what is often referred to as a bad trip.&nbsp;﻿<br><br></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Preparation</h4>\n<p>The preparation of a session includes the gathering of the required knowledge for the experience as well as laying down the ground rules for what is possible or what is desired in the session.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<p>This might include the various practicalities of working with your guide, establishing your mind-set for the session and defining or clarifying the intention. In most psychedelic sessions it\'s important to establish the \"why\" for the session. Having a clear intention can help the mind to focus on the reason why you have launched into the sometimes confusing psychedelic landscape.﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Session<br></h4>\n<p>The session itself is often seen as the focus for the therapy but it is ultimately just a part of it. It\'s relatively easy to overlook the other components of the process (ie preparation and integration) given our natural focus on having the experience but the real benefit of working with non-ordinary states is found in what happens afterwards.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Even though the experience itself can be profoundly life changing it is how we are able to put the insight gained during the session into practice that can help us to&nbsp;reap the benefits of the non-ordinary state.﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Integration<br></h4>\n<p>Integration is essentially the process of embodying the wisdom and insight gained during the psychedelic session. How this process unfolds&nbsp;depends on a number of factors. Questions that may be helpful for preparing for integration may include:</p>\n<ul><li>﻿What supports do you have to work through the material that arose in the session?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you have people close to you that you can talk to?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you have daily practices such as meditation, journalling, or other physical practices?</li><li> Do you have good physical therapists or psychotherapists to work with after the session?</li><li>Have you allowed for enough time and space after the session?</li><li>Do you have <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/resources\" target=\"_blank\">cognitive resources and frameworks</a> that may help you to understand the experience?</li></ul>\n<p>The time taken to integrate a non-ordinary state of consciousness really depends on the nature of the experience and the supports you have around you. Some experiences may be able to be integrated within the session itself while&nbsp;others may literally take years.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿Ultimately the integration of non-ordinary states of experience is very personal and may include a wide range of supports and practices.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/jr-korpa-yhDnHJybJms-unsplash_s0qxsy\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n             <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/ilya-lix-QAj0DLBJ974-unsplash_pmlhme\" data-image=\"gdwc0edytmgd\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>How can psychotherapy support the<br> integration of psychedelic experiences?</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Psychotherapy and breath work can be supportive relational and experiential&nbsp;tools to work with the integration of non-ordinary states of consciousness.</p></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Sharing the story ...</h3></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>The psychedelic experience can often be confusing and hard to make sense of, and so the sharing of the story of your experience and being listened to&nbsp;in a non-directive / non-judgemental / curious way, can often allow the really important parts of the experience come to the surface. This ideally&nbsp;supports the individual to find their own meaning or wisdom from their experience and to create reference points or \"touch stones\" that help with the integration.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sharing. the story is less about finding a narrative for the experience but to uncover themes and plumb the depths of the \"feeling\" of the experience. In the words of Tav Sparks, \"<i>Feeling is the royal road to healing</i>\" and as such the feeling in the experience can help us to connect with other thematically linked&nbsp;material we may be working with in our life.</p></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Somatic exploration ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Bessel Van Der Kolks book,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Body-Keeps-Score-Healing-Trauma/dp/0143127748\" target=\"_blank\">The body keeps the score</a>&nbsp;</i>﻿emphatically describes&nbsp;the role of the body in healing trauma; Working with non-ordinary states of consciousness is no different. After a breathwork or psychedelic session we can work with the body using breath, guided imagery and felt sensation to help bring any parts of the experience into a point of&nbsp;completion. The psyche is always trying to move us towards wholeness and so using a simple body scan and gentle breathing technique we can unlock this potential and help to further re-member or somatise the psychedelic experience.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Holotropic Breathwork&nbsp; ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>In some cases the psychedelic experience may be somewhat incomplete and more non-ordinary states of consciousness work may be an important part of the integration process. This is especially true if the psychedelic experience was disrupted, held in an unsafe container or the material that emerged was too much to fully digest within a single session.</p>\n<p>﻿Holotropic Breathwork can often help the breather to resolve or bring to a point of completion (within a greater circle of incompletion) the material that was opened up to in the psychedelic session.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Integrating a bad trip ...</h3>\n<h4>﻿From a Holotropic breathwork or transpersonal lens there may indeed be no such thing as a \"bad trip\" - but there are most definitely experiences that are <i>extremely</i> difficult to experience and even more difficult to integrate.&nbsp;</h4>\n<p>Excluding experiences that are held in unsafe environments, or without the proper preparation or supervision, any non-ordinary state of consciousness has the potential to help us heal. The material that emerges in the session&nbsp;can be seen as the psyche attempting to move towards wholeness, regardless of the quality or the type of&nbsp;material that is emerging.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This means that any part of the personal or collective experience can become manifest in the psychedelic journey. And because of the nature of the psychedelic experience this&nbsp;may lead to frightening, existential or terrifying experiences that confront the journeyer with their deepest fears in a very phenomenal way.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The non-ordinary state is often a way for the psyche to seek the&nbsp;deep integration of its shadow.&nbsp;&nbsp;By its very nature the shadow can be terrifying, as it contains all of the parts of ourselves that we are no yet able to or willing to&nbsp;see.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿Integrating difficult trips can be made even more challenging because of the shame and guilt the journeyer may experience after the session. Non-ordinary states are not especially well held in the Western worldview and difficult non-ordinary states are even less so. However if we can approach the difficult&nbsp;experience with an open and curious mind and be willing to. work through our reaction to the experience, the difficult psychedelic experience may in fact yield more benefit than the classical cosmic journey.﻿<br></p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>﻿Disclaimer</h4>\n<p>Due to the legal status of psychedelic assisted therapy,&nbsp;﻿Anthony is not available as a guide for psychedelic therapy sessions. If you would like supporting in working with psychedelic integration please get in touch or book an appointment below.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/adrien-converse-xzH7K6nVVgI-unsplash_gh4j6b\" data-image=\"kxo1qcexzy6s\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo uk-light\" style=\"background-color: rgb(55, 71, 79);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>My Holotropic Breathwork experience</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork has been a fundamental influence on how I&nbsp;﻿approach all aspects of my life and indeed since the late 1990\'s it has been the primary tool I&nbsp;﻿have used in order to gain greater insight into my life.</p>\n<p>﻿My work with Alf Foote was foundational in terms of demonstrating the transformative potential of the breath. And from 2006 to 2013 my training to become a Holotropic Breathwork facilitator via <a href=\"http://holotropic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GTT</a>&nbsp;further grounded my understanding of the healing power of non-ordinary states of consciousness.</p>\n<p>﻿Since 2013 I&nbsp;﻿have been running Holotropic Breathwork Workshops in Melbourne with <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/practitioners/ruth-langford\" target=\"_blank\">Ruth Langford</a> and others and have also been on staff as a part of the <a href=\"https://holotropic.com.au/training\" target=\"_blank\">Grof Transpersonal Training programs</a> in Australia.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Holotropic Breathwork is held in workshops and smallgroups</h4></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>For a schedule of upcoming workshops and groups please visit the <a href=\"http://melbournebreathwork.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Melbourne Breathwork website</a>.&nbsp; Workshops will re-commence in February 2021.﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/workshops\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">VIEW UPCOMING EVENTS</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/r_0/1042/IMG_1025_v3lm0h\" data-image=\"riefmxhq4izs\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-auto uk-flex-top padding-large with-redo has-section-width-uk-container\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>﻿Make a booking</b></h2>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><iframe src=\"https://app.squarespacescheduling.com/schedule.php?owner=21951962&amp;owner=21951962&amp;appointmentType=33337327\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></figure></div>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'fly-d-xcG3Yg6iCQg-unsplash_slfqyx', 1042, 1, 'It\'s no secret that psychedelics have been undergoing a resurgence in popular culture over the last decade. New science has been revealing what psychonauts through the ages of known - that psychedelic and non-ordinary states have an enormous power to change, shape and re-frame our lives. However the question remains - what do we do with the experience?', 'Psychedelic Integration: Harnessing the Power of Non-Ordinary States', NULL, 'Explore the power of psychedelics and non-ordinary states to shape your life. Learn about psychedelic sessions, their components, and the importance of preparation and integration.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:29', 3, NULL, 36, NULL, 1, 18, NULL, 0, NULL),
	(3008, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Resources', 'resources', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>Resources</h1></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"8\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"List\" data-source=\"Pages\">[widget:8|List|Pages]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'wolf-medicine_wy2wzj', 1314, 1, '', 'Top Resources | Comprehensive Guides and Tips', NULL, 'Explore our extensive resources for insightful articles, valuable tips, and detailed guides to enhance your knowledge and skills.', '2025-07-04 07:50:25', '2026-01-05 00:10:29', 0, NULL, 4, NULL, 0, 21, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3012, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 0, 'Generated Article on Breathwork, Bodywork, Emotional Healing, Psychological Insight', 'generated-article-on-breathwork-bodywork-emotional-healing-psychological-insight', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/melissa-askew-8n00CqwnqO8-unsplash_r8kqbk\" data-image=\"ai-generated-1\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Embracing the Power of Breath: The Magic of Breathwork</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>At the core of our existence is breath, the life-giving force that fuels our body and mind. Yet, how often do we take conscious notice of this automatic process? That\'s where breathwork comes in.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Breathwork is a practice that involves conscious and controlled breathing to influence your mental, emotional, and physical state. It\'s like yoga for your breathing, training the respiratory muscles, and bringing awareness to the breath\'s ebb and flow.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Through various breathing techniques, individuals can tap into their emotional and psychological depths, releasing pent-up emotions, reducing stress, and even achieving profound states of relaxation and clarity. It\'s a journey of self-discovery, where each breath sheds light on hidden corners of the psyche and opens avenues for emotional healing.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>The Symbiotic Dance of Breathwork and Bodywork</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>While breathwork lays the groundwork for self-exploration, bodywork complements this journey by physically releasing the tensions stored in our bodies. Techniques such as massage, acupuncture, and chiropractic adjustments fall under the umbrella of bodywork. These practices work to alleviate physical discomfort and promote relaxation, which in turn, supports emotional balance.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>When combined, breathwork and bodywork create a harmonious duo, each enhancing the effects of the other. As you engage in breathwork, your body becomes more receptive to the benefits of bodywork. Conversely, the physical release achieved through bodywork can make the breathwork experience more profound and impactful.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Breathing Your Way to Emotional Healing and Psychological Insight</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>So, how exactly can these practices contribute to emotional healing and psychological insight? The answer lies in their ability to create a bridge between the mind and the body. By focusing on the breath and physical sensations, individuals can become more aware of their emotional states, and gain insight into their psychological patterns.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>For instance, a person may notice that specific emotions are accompanied by particular breathing patterns or physical sensations. Recognizing these correlations can provide valuable psychological insights and promote emotional healing by enabling individuals to process and release these feelings consciously.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>The beauty of breathwork and bodywork lies in their accessibility. You don\'t need any special equipment or a dedicated space. All you need is your breath, your body, and an open mind. So, why not give it a try? Breathe deep, release tension, and embark on a journey of self-discovery and healing.</p></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2025-07-08 23:25:29', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'melissa-askew-8n00CqwnqO8-unsplash_r8kqbk', 1314, 1, '{\n  \"title\": \"Unleashing the Power of Breathwork and Bodywork for Emotional Healing\",\n  \"page_title\": \"Harnessing Breathwork and Bodywork for Emotional Healing and Psychological Insight\",\n  \"page_desc', '', NULL, '', '2025-07-08 23:25:29', '2025-07-09 06:32:49', 0, 1, 51, '2025-07-09 06:32:49', 0, 50, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3016, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Unleash Your Inner Harmony: The Magic of Breathwork Music', 'unleash-your-inner-harmony-the-magic-of-breathwork-music', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751242022/1314/ohbw_d0ri3p.jpg\" data-image=\"ai-generated-0\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What&#039;s the Buzz About Breathwork Music?</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Well, you\'re not alone in embracing this trend. Breathwork music is gaining popularity worldwide, and for good reasons. This unique blend of rhythmic tunes and guided breathing exercises is a powerful tool in managing stress and promoting overall wellness.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>But Why Music, You Ask?</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Music, with its universal language, has the <a href=\"/healthy-masculinity-the-power-of-mens-groups-in-collective-healing\">power</a> to stir emotions, trigger memories, and even alter our mood. Combine this with the therapeutic benefits of breathwork, and you\'ve got a match made in heaven! Harmonious tunes can guide your breathing rhythm, help you focus, and create a tranquil atmosphere for your breathwork sessions.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751242022/1314/ohbw_d0ri3p.jpg\" data-image=\"ai-generated-1\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Bringing Breathwork Music into Your Daily Routine</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Now that you\'re intrigued, let\'s look at how to incorporate breathwork music into your daily routine. <a href=\"/holotropic-breathwork-its-potential-life-changing-impact\">it\'s</a> easier than you might think. All you need is a quiet space, your favorite relaxing music, and an open mind.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Step 1: Choose Your Music</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Start by selecting music that resonates with you. It could be soothing instrumental tracks, nature sounds, or specially designed breathwork music available online. Remember, it\'s all about what makes you feel relaxed and centered.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Step 2: Set the Scene</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Create a calm and comfortable environment. Dim the lights, light a scented candle if you like, and ensure you won\'t be disturbed. Now, hit play on your music and get ready to <a href=\"/breathe-your-way-to-balance-the-polyvagal-theory-and-meditation\">breathe</a>.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Step 3: Breathe with the Rhythm</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Close your eyes, listen to the music, and start to focus on your breathing. Notice the sounds, the rhythm, and how they guide your breaths. You\'ll soon find yourself immersed in a calming, meditative state that leaves you feeling refreshed and rejuvenated.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751242022/1314/ohbw_d0ri3p.jpg\" data-image=\"ai-generated-2\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Take a Musical Breath for Better Health</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>So, there you have it! Breathwork music is not only a delightful listening experience but also a powerful health and wellness tool. By incorporating it into your routine, you\'re taking a positive step towards stress management, mental clarity, and overall well-being. So go ahead, take a deep musical breath, and let the harmony within you shine!</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n', '2025-07-09 11:51:49', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'ohbw_d0ri3p', 1314, 1, 'Uncover the benefits of breathwork music and learn how to seamlessly incorporate this powerful wellness tool into your everyday life.', '', NULL, '', '2025-07-09 11:51:49', '2025-07-09 11:52:15', 0, 1, 55, '2025-07-09 11:52:15', 1, 54, NULL, 0, NULL),
	(3021, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Psychedelic Integration', 'psychedelic-integration-osgk', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large uk-flex-middle with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Psychedelic Integration</h1>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\">\n                        Integrating non-ordinary states of consciousness</h2></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>It\'s no secret that psychedelics have been undergoing a resurgence in popular culture over the last decade. New science has been revealing what psychonauts through the ages of known - that psychedelic and non-ordinary states have an enormous power to change, shape and re-frame our lives. However the question remains - what do we do with the experience?</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3><b>What are the components of a psychedelic session?</b><br></h3>\n<p>Any experience involving&nbsp;non-ordinary state of consciousness can be broken into 3 parts:</p>\n<ol><li>Preparation</li><li>﻿Session</li><li>﻿﻿Integration</li></ol>\n<p>﻿Without the proper attention to any of these three parts there is a much greater potential for fragmentation, de-stabilisation or what is often referred to as a bad trip.&nbsp;﻿<br><br></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Preparation</h4>\n<p>The preparation of a session includes the gathering of the required knowledge for the experience as well as laying down the ground rules for what is possible or what is desired in the session.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<p>This might include the various practicalities of working with your guide, establishing your mind-set for the session and defining or clarifying the intention. In most psychedelic sessions it\'s important to establish the \"why\" for the session. Having a clear intention can help the mind to focus on the reason why you have launched into the sometimes confusing psychedelic landscape.﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Session<br></h4>\n<p>The session itself is often seen as the focus for the therapy but it is ultimately just a part of it. It\'s relatively easy to overlook the other components of the process (ie preparation and integration) given our natural focus on having the experience but the real benefit of working with non-ordinary states is found in what happens afterwards.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Even though the experience itself can be profoundly life changing it is how we are able to put the insight gained during the session into practice that can help us to&nbsp;reap the benefits of the non-ordinary state.﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>Integration<br></h4>\n<p>Integration is essentially the process of embodying the wisdom and insight gained during the psychedelic session. How this process unfolds&nbsp;depends on a number of factors. Questions that may be helpful for preparing for integration may include:</p>\n<ul><li>﻿What supports do you have to work through the material that arose in the session?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you have people close to you that you can talk to?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you have daily practices such as meditation, journalling, or other physical practices?</li><li> Do you have good physical therapists or psychotherapists to work with after the session?</li><li>Have you allowed for enough time and space after the session?</li><li>Do you have <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com/resources\" target=\"_blank\">cognitive resources and frameworks</a> that may help you to understand the experience?</li></ul>\n<p>The time taken to integrate a non-ordinary state of consciousness really depends on the nature of the experience and the supports you have around you. Some experiences may be able to be integrated within the session itself while&nbsp;others may literally take years.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿Ultimately the integration of non-ordinary states of experience is very personal and may include a wide range of supports and practices.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/jr-korpa-yhDnHJybJms-unsplash_s0qxsy\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n             <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/ilya-lix-QAj0DLBJ974-unsplash_pmlhme\" data-image=\"gdwc0edytmgd\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>How can psychotherapy support the<br> integration of psychedelic experiences?</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Psychotherapy and breath work can be supportive relational and experiential&nbsp;tools to work with the integration of non-ordinary states of consciousness.</p></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Sharing the story ...</h3></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>The psychedelic experience can often be confusing and hard to make sense of, and so the sharing of the story of your experience and being listened to&nbsp;in a non-directive / non-judgemental / curious way, can often allow the really important parts of the experience come to the surface. This ideally&nbsp;supports the individual to find their own meaning or wisdom from their experience and to create reference points or \"touch stones\" that help with the integration.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sharing. the story is less about finding a narrative for the experience but to uncover themes and plumb the depths of the \"feeling\" of the experience. In the words of Tav Sparks, \"<i>Feeling is the royal road to healing</i>\" and as such the feeling in the experience can help us to connect with other thematically linked&nbsp;material we may be working with in our life.</p></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Somatic exploration ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Bessel Van Der Kolks book,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Body-Keeps-Score-Healing-Trauma/dp/0143127748\" target=\"_blank\">The body keeps the score</a>&nbsp;</i>﻿emphatically describes&nbsp;the role of the body in healing trauma; Working with non-ordinary states of consciousness is no different. After a breathwork or psychedelic session we can work with the body using breath, guided imagery and felt sensation to help bring any parts of the experience into a point of&nbsp;completion. The psyche is always trying to move us towards wholeness and so using a simple body scan and gentle breathing technique we can unlock this potential and help to further re-member or somatise the psychedelic experience.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Holotropic Breathwork&nbsp; ...</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>In some cases the psychedelic experience may be somewhat incomplete and more non-ordinary states of consciousness work may be an important part of the integration process. This is especially true if the psychedelic experience was disrupted, held in an unsafe container or the material that emerged was too much to fully digest within a single session.</p>\n<p>﻿Holotropic Breathwork can often help the breather to resolve or bring to a point of completion (within a greater circle of incompletion) the material that was opened up to in the psychedelic session.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-2_1-2\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Integrating a bad trip ...</h3>\n<h4>﻿From a Holotropic breathwork or transpersonal lens there may indeed be no such thing as a \"bad trip\" - but there are most definitely experiences that are <i>extremely</i> difficult to experience and even more difficult to integrate.&nbsp;</h4>\n<p>Excluding experiences that are held in unsafe environments, or without the proper preparation or supervision, any non-ordinary state of consciousness has the potential to help us heal. The material that emerges in the session&nbsp;can be seen as the psyche attempting to move towards wholeness, regardless of the quality or the type of&nbsp;material that is emerging.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This means that any part of the personal or collective experience can become manifest in the psychedelic journey. And because of the nature of the psychedelic experience this&nbsp;may lead to frightening, existential or terrifying experiences that confront the journeyer with their deepest fears in a very phenomenal way.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The non-ordinary state is often a way for the psyche to seek the&nbsp;deep integration of its shadow.&nbsp;&nbsp;By its very nature the shadow can be terrifying, as it contains all of the parts of ourselves that we are no yet able to or willing to&nbsp;see.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿Integrating difficult trips can be made even more challenging because of the shame and guilt the journeyer may experience after the session. Non-ordinary states are not especially well held in the Western worldview and difficult non-ordinary states are even less so. However if we can approach the difficult&nbsp;experience with an open and curious mind and be willing to. work through our reaction to the experience, the difficult psychedelic experience may in fact yield more benefit than the classical cosmic journey.﻿<br></p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>﻿Disclaimer</h4>\n<p>Due to the legal status of psychedelic assisted therapy,&nbsp;﻿Anthony is not available as a guide for psychedelic therapy sessions. If you would like supporting in working with psychedelic integration please get in touch or book an appointment below.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-2@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/adrien-converse-xzH7K6nVVgI-unsplash_gh4j6b\" data-image=\"kxo1qcexzy6s\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'fly-d-xcG3Yg6iCQg-unsplash_slfqyx', 1042, 1, 'It\'s no secret that psychedelics have been undergoing a resurgence in popular culture over the last decade. New science has been revealing what psychonauts through the ages of known - that psychedelic and non-ordinary states have an enormous power to change, shape and re-frame our lives. However the question remains - what do we do with the experience?', 'Psychedelic Integration: Understanding &amp; Maximizing Non-Ordinary States', NULL, 'Explore the power of psychedelic integration and non-ordinary states of consciousness. Learn the importance of preparation, session, and integration for a transformative experience and how to effectively apply the insights gained.', '2025-07-10 05:12:28', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 48, NULL, 55, NULL, 0, 4, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3022, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Workshops', 'workshops', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/c_fill,h_300,w_500,x_300,y_300/asset-library/niko-soikkeli-333391_hibqhy\" data-image=\"jcuaolf758dc\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Workshops</h2></div>\n                        </div>                                                                                                                                                                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"11\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"List\" data-source=\"Pages\">[widget:11|List|Pages]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'mohamed-nohassi-odxB5oIG_iA-unsplash_r49u8y', 1314, 1, '', 'Interactive Workshops - Enhance Your Skills Today', NULL, 'Dive into our wide range of workshops designed to boost your knowledge and skills. Explore our list of workshops now.', '2025-07-10 05:34:27', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 0, NULL, 56, NULL, 0, 65, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3023, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'About', 'about', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/c_fill,h_300,w_500,x_300,y_300/asset-library/jesse-bowser-258699-unsplash_ejqvr1\" data-image=\"2bhjwd5zal7o\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>About Me</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>{%about%}</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Qualifications</h2></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>{%qualifications%}</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2025-07-10 05:36:48', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'wolf-medicine_wy2wzj', 1314, 1, '', 'About', NULL, '', '2025-07-10 05:36:58', '2025-09-01 00:10:43', 0, NULL, 57, '2025-09-01 00:10:43', 0, 2, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3024, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Couples Breathwork Therapy Sessions', 'couples-breathwork-therapy', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large uk-flex-middle with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1\">\n            <div class=\"uk-container\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_800/1042/daniel-j-schwarz-YtY724tdl7Y-unsplash_q9d47g\" style=\"margin-top:1.5em\" data-image=\"qnh4z6inv9rw\" alt=\"\" class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\"></figure></div></div></div></div></div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\"><div class=\"grid-inner\"><div class=\"uk-sortable\"><div class=\"content-block\"><div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 class=\"uk-margin-remove-bottom\">\n                        Holotropic Breathwork for Couples</h1>\n<h2 class=\"uk-margin-remove-top\">\n                        Combining Holotropic Breathwork with ongoing couples work to expand and deepen connection, communication and understanding</h2></div></div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Couples therapy is a powerful tool that helps couples improve their relationship by providing them with the tools and skills they need to communicate effectively, resolve conflicts, and build a stronger bond. However, for couples who are looking for a more transformative and holistic approach to therapy, Holotropic Breathwork is an exciting option to consider.</p>\n<p>Holotropic Breathwork is a form of therapy that combines deep breathing techniques, music, and bodywork to access the deeper parts of the psyche. It was developed by Stanislav Grof, a Czech psychiatrist who spent decades researching non-ordinary states of consciousness, and it is based on the idea that the human psyche has the innate ability to heal itself.</p>\n<p>When combined with couples therapy, Holotropic Breathwork can help couples access deeper levels of awareness and understanding, leading to greater self-awareness and improved communication. Here are some of the ways that couples therapy combined with Holotropic Breathwork can benefit your relationship:</p>\n<h2><b>1. Increased emotional intimacy&nbsp;</b></h2>\n<p><b></b>Holotropic Breathwork can help couples connect on a deeper emotional level, allowing them to access feelings and emotions that may be difficult to articulate. By engaging in this practice together, couples can create a safe and supportive environment where they can explore their feelings and connect with each other in a more meaningful way.</p>\n<h2><b>2. Greater self-awareness&nbsp;</b></h2>\n<p><b></b>Through Holotropic Breathwork, couples can gain a greater understanding of their own thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. This increased self-awareness can help them identify patterns in their relationship that may be holding them back and make the necessary changes to improve their relationship.</p>\n<h2><b>3. Improved communication</b>&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>Holotropic Breathwork can help couples improve their communication skills by providing them with a deeper understanding of their own emotions and needs. This increased awareness can lead to more open and honest communication, which can strengthen the bond between partners and reduce conflict.</p>\n<h2><b>4. Deeper empathy</b>&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>By experiencing non-ordinary states of consciousness together, couples can develop a greater sense of empathy for each other. This can help them understand each other\'s perspectives and feelings on a deeper level, leading to a more compassionate and supportive relationship.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div>\n                </div>\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n<div class=\"content-row-overlay\" style=\"display: none;\">\n        </div></div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n             <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/Therapy-couch_blnacf\" data-image=\"gdwc0edytmgd\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What is involved with&nbsp;Holotropic Breathwork for couples therapy?</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Holotropic Breathwork for couples therapy includes 3 sessions:</p>\n<h4><b>﻿Session 1</b> - Introduction and preparation (50 Minutes)</h4>\n<p>﻿During the integration and preparation session we will discuss the various themes that are emerging in the relationship and how they are impacting the relationship. We will also discuss the theory and practice of Holotropic Breathwork and how breathwork may support the working through of those themes.</p>\n<h4>﻿<b>﻿Session 2</b> - The breathwork session day. (10am to 4:30pm).</h4>\n<p>﻿This is a whole day of breathwork where you will take part in two breathwork sessions. Each breathwork session will run for 2.5 hours and you will have an opportunity to sit for your partner while they breathe and they will sit for you while you breathe. The process of sitting in breathwork is often described as being just as powerful as the breathwork process itself.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>﻿There will be an opportunity to integration work on the day after each session as well as time for lunch.</p>\n<h4><b>﻿Session 3&nbsp;</b>﻿- Integration (50 Minutes)<br></h4>\n<p>The ﻿integration phase for any non-ordinary states of awareness work is crucial as it helps us to make sense of the experience and too help us to understand how we might be able to bring the wisdom and insight from the experience into our daily lives and importantly into our relationships.</p>\n<p>﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                \n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>Who is this suited for?</b></h2>\n<p>﻿While breathwork may well be a powerful tool for developing self awareness it is not always the right choice for some individuals. Ideally couples who attend this couples breathwork work are already in some form of couples or individual counselling, have a degree of communication skills within the relationship.</p>\n<p>﻿A key factor of suitability for couples doing this work is that there are no occurrences of domestic violence nor the threat of such violence. For non-ordinary state work to be truly supportive&nbsp;the container the work is performed in must have some capacity for each party to take ownership of their experience and that there be limited projection onto the other of that experience. If you are interested in doing this work but are not sure if this is right for you, you may like to book a <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/book-an-introductory-chat\">﻿free 20 minute introductory phone﻿</a> call where we can discuss those concerns.﻿<b>﻿</b></p></div>\n                        </div>                                                                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><b>Pricing Structure</b><br></h2>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">The cost of the&nbsp;whole package including introduction, session and integration is $1200.</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\">Bookings can be made for the first introductory session via my appointments page.</a>﻿.</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿At the end of that session we will book in a time to complete the rest of the sessions.﻿﻿﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\"><b>﻿Cancellation Fee:</b></h2>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿Introductory and integration sessions have a standard $160 cancellation fee within 24 hours.﻿﻿﻿</p>\n<p data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">﻿Breathwork sessions have a $200 cancellation fee within 72 hours of the session.</p></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/melissa-askew-8n00CqwnqO8-unsplash_r8kqbk\" data-image=\"kxo1qcexzy6s\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'daniel-j-schwarz-YtY724tdl7Y-unsplash_q9d47g', 1042, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork for Couples\nCombining Holotropic Breathwork with ongoing couples work to expand and deepen connection, communication and understanding', 'Holotropic Breathwork: Transformative Couples Therapy Sessions', NULL, 'Discover the transformative power of Holotropic Breathwork in couples therapy. Enhance communication, deepen emotional connection and gain self-awareness for a healthier relationship. Explore the benefits of this holistic approach to couples therapy.', '2025-07-10 05:42:47', '2026-01-23 21:25:20', 48, NULL, 58, NULL, 0, 9, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3025, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Brunswick Psychotherapy and Counselling', 'brunswick-psychotherapy-and-counselling', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-40 uk-flex-middle padding-large with-redo has-section-width-uk-container-large row-columns-1-3_2-3\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1661211730/1042/jr-korpa-yhDnHJybJms-unsplash_s0qxsy.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"3dytms557z8w\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Psychotherapy &amp; Counselling in Brunswick</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">I offer one-on-one counselling and psychotherapy sessions in Brunswick, working with people who are ready to develop greater awareness, process unresolved experiences, and build better relationships.</h3></div>\n</div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>How I Work</h2>\n<p>My approach draws from Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal methods. These are experiential sessions that include your mind, body, and spirit in addressing whatever you bring. Rather than just talking, we might work with breathing, body awareness, dreams, or other ways of exploring what\'s present for you.</p>\n<p>Each session is shaped by what emerges and what feels most helpful in the moment. Some people find this different from traditional talk therapy, and that\'s intentional—I believe healing happens through the whole person, not just through thinking about problems.﻿<br></p>\n<p></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>What People Bring to Sessions</h2>\n<p>I work with people experiencing:</p>\n<ul><li>Anxiety and depression</li><li>Trauma and its effects</li><li>Grief and loss</li><li>Physical pain that seems connected to emotional experiences</li><li>Relationship patterns they want to understand or change</li><li>A desire for psychological integration</li><li>Interest in shadow work—exploring parts of themselves they\'ve pushed away</li><li>Simply wanting to explore their inner world more deeply﻿</li></ul></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>About the Process</h2>\n<p>Sessions are experiential, which means we work with what\'s actually happening in the present moment. This might include noticing body sensations, following your breath, exploring a feeling, or working with imagery. I pay attention to the whole person—not just your words, but how you sit, breathe, and move through the world.</p>\n<p>Some sessions involve breathwork. Others focus on dialogue between different parts of yourself. We might explore dreams, work with creative expression, or simply sit with what\'s present. The approach adapts to what you need.﻿<br></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Location and Community</h2>\n<p></p>\n<p>You can find us at 503 Sydney Road, Brunswick, near the corner of Blythe Street and Sydney Road. The area has a good mix of creativity and groundedness that fits well with this kind of work.</p>\n<p><strong>Parking:</strong> There is 2-hour parking available on Sydney Road, but please note the clearway times—city bound in the morning and on the other side in the afternoon. Plan accordingly to avoid any parking issues.</p>\n<p>I serve people from across Melbourne\'s inner north, with clients coming from Brunswick, Fitzroy, Carlton, Coburg, and other nearby areas.﻿<br></p>\n<p></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Getting Started</h2>\n<p>If you\'re curious about this approach or think it might be helpful for what you\'re experiencing, we can start with a conversation. I\'m happy to discuss what you\'re looking for and whether working together makes sense.</p>\n<p>The work requires some openness to exploring beyond just talking, but you don\'t need any special experience or preparation. You just need to be willing to see what emerges when we create space for it.</p>\n<p><br></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>﻿<strong>Professional counselling and psychotherapy in Brunswick, incorporating mind, body, and spirit approaches to healing.</strong></h2></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-auto uk-dark padding-large uk-flex-top overlay-none with-redo\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Melbourne Processwork - psychotherapy and counselling in Brunswick</h2></div>\n                        </div>\n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block widget-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><div data-num=\"1\" id=\"widget-creator\" data-title=\"Page Widget\" data-widget=\"1\" data-cat=\"0\">\n			<div data-mode=\"readonly\" data-active=\"0\" class=\"content-wrap widget-item\">\n				<span data-id=\"12\" class=\"widget-code-holder\" data-redactor-span=\"true\" data-type=\"Map\" data-source=\"Clinic Address\">[widget:12|Map|Clinic Address]</span>\n			</div>\n		</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 30px;\">You can find us at 503 Sydney Rd, Brunswick. Near the corner of Blythe St and Sydney Rd.</h4>\n<p>﻿Please note that while there is 2 hour parking on Sydney rd it is a clearway city bound in the morning and a clearway on the otherside in the afternoon.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'pat-whelen-AWm4F-QcgkE-unsplash_gk09mt', 1042, 1, 'My approach draws from Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal methods. These are experiential sessions that include your mind, body, and spirit in addressing whatever you bring. Rather than just talking, we might work with breathing, body awareness, dreams, or other ways of exploring what\'s present for you.\n\nEach session is shaped by what emerges and what feels most helpful in the moment. Some people find this different from traditional talk therapy, and that\'s intentional—I believe healing happens through the whole person, not just through thinking about problems.', 'Brunswick Psychotherapy & Counselling - Personalized Therapy Sessions', NULL, 'Offering personalized psychotherapy & counselling in Brunswick, using a blend of Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal methods to help you gain self-awareness, process experiences, and improve relationships. Located at 503 Sydney Road, Brunswick.', '2025-07-10 07:54:02', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 0, NULL, 59, NULL, 0, 66, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3070, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Upcoming workshops', 'upcoming-workshops', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 padding-small with-redo row-columns-1-4 has-section-width-uk-container\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 style=\"margin-top: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 30px;\">Workshops</h1></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>I facilitate Holotropic Breathwork workshops and men’s groups through <a href=\"https://melbourneprocesswork.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Melbourne Breathwork</a>. Our workshops offer a supportive group setting for deep inner exploration, using connected breathing, evocative music, and a safely held space to encourage personal insight and healing.</p>\n<p>Workshops are usually held over one or two days in Hawthorn and include preparation, two breathwork sessions, and time for integration. No previous experience is necessary—just a willingness to be present with the process. Grounded in the work of Stanislav and Christina Grof, sessions are facilitated by experienced practitioners trained in this approach.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            \n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>{%feed|domain:melbournebreathwork.com|model:events|filter:future|layout:calendar%} </p></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'cynthia-magana-mFPJXEQfb9M-unsplash_dzpjbc_l83k0a', 1314, 1, '', 'Psychotherapy Services | Wild Heart Psychotherapy', NULL, 'Experience grounded, respectful psychotherapy at Wild Heart Psychotherapy. We offer support for anxiety, depression, grief, and life transitions. Connect today for an initial chat or to book a session.', '2025-08-03 04:58:08', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 0, NULL, 65, NULL, 0, 67, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3075, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Holotropic Breathwork: A Journey into Healing and Understanding Body Physiology', 'holotropic-breathwork-a-journey-into-healing-and-understanding-body-physiology', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751424289/1314/wolf-medicine_wy2wzj.png\" data-image=\"ai-generated-0\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Embarking on the Holotropic Breathwork Journey</h2></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751424289/1314/wolf-medicine_wy2wzj.png\" data-image=\"ai-generated-1\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Understanding Holotropic Breathwork</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Originally developed by psychiatrists Stanislav and Christina Grof in the 1970s, Holotropic Breathwork is a therapeutic practice that involves using breathing techniques to promote emotional healing and self-understanding. In essence, it\'s a way of using your <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/the-magic-of-breathwork-and-music-a-journey-into-trance\">breath</a> to tap into your subconscious, unveiling patterns, traumas, and insights that may be hidden deep within.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751424289/1314/wolf-medicine_wy2wzj.png\" data-image=\"ai-generated-2\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>How Holotropic Breathwork Influences Healing</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>What\'s particularly intriguing about this practice is its potential in facilitating healing. Let\'s take, for instance, someone dealing with emotional trauma or stress. By using Holotropic Breathwork, they can potentially reach into their subconscious, confront these issues, and begin the healing process. It\'s not a magic cure-all, mind you, but it\'s a tool that can contribute to the journey of healing.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751424289/1314/wolf-medicine_wy2wzj.png\" data-image=\"ai-generated-3\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Connecting Breathwork and Body Physiology</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Now, you might be wondering how breathing can have such profound effects. This is where body physiology comes into play. When we alter our breathing patterns, it directly impacts our physiological state. For example, slow, deep breaths can stimulate the parasympathetic nervous system, promoting relaxation and reducing stress. In the context of Holotropic Breathwork, the specific breathing techniques used can help induce a state of heightened awareness or altered consciousness, which could potentially allow for deeper introspection and healing.</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\">\n                                <figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n                                    <img class=\"\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/v1751424289/1314/wolf-medicine_wy2wzj.png\" data-image=\"ai-generated-4\">\n                                </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <h1 class=\"font-bold mb-4\">{%title%}</h1>\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Experiencing Holotropic Breathwork</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Experiencing Holotropic Breathwork is something deeply <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/holotropic-breathwork-its-potential-life-changing-impact\">personal</a> and can vary from <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\">person</a> to person. Some may find it transformative, while others might not feel much difference. But one thing\'s for sure, it\'s a journey into the self, an exploration of your inner world. It\'s not about chasing a \'high\' or seeking an escape, but about deepening your understanding of yourself and your body.</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3 class=\'mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-100\'>Possibly Related Content</h3></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/holotropic-breathwork-its-potential-life-changing-impact\">Holotropic Breathwork &amp; it\'s potential life changing impact</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/holotropic-breathwork\">Holotropic Breathwork</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/discover-your-inner-healer-a-guide-to-holistic-healing-and-breathwork\">Discover Your Inner Healer: A Guide to Holistic Healing and Breathwork</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/the-magic-of-breathwork-and-music-a-journey-into-trance\">The Magic of Breathwork and Music: A Journey into Trance</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/resources/healthy-masculinity-the-power-of-mens-groups-in-collective-healing\">Healthy Masculinity: The Power of Men\'s Groups in Collective Healing</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>\n\n', '2025-08-04 02:11:38', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'wolf-medicine_wy2wzj', 1314, 1, 'Explore the intriguing practice of Holotropic Breathwork, its role in promoting emotional healing, and its connection to body physiology.', '', NULL, '', '2025-08-04 02:11:38', '2025-08-04 02:14:43', 0, 1, 67, '2025-08-04 02:14:43', 1, 65, NULL, 0, NULL),
	(3090, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Lorne', 'lorne-psychotherapy', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex row-columns-1-3_2-3 with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large\" style=\"\n    /* margin-top: -50px; */\n\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\" style=\"\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/anthony-avatar-large-anthony-olsen-1080x675_xmdgo9_ynyj1z_5f2vrU_ouiqt4\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"nm6rkrh3hsip\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div>                        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\" class=\"w-full uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">BOOK A SESSION IN LORNE</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 30px;\"><p>“If we surrendered to earth’s intelligence we could rise up rooted, like trees.”&nbsp;</p></blockquote></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p class=\"uppercase text-sm mt-4\" style=\"text-align: right;margin-top:0\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"text-align: right;margin-top:0\"><i>- Rainer Maria Rilke</i></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\" style=\"\n    margin-top: -50px;\n\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin-top: 30px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin-top: 30px;\">From February 2026, I will be offering psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork sessions in Lorne on the Surf Coast of Victoria.</h2>\n<p>﻿Alongside my Melbourne practice in Brunswick, this expands my work into the surrounds of the Erskine River rainforest, providing a quieter regional setting for depth-oriented psychotherapy and individual breathwork.</p>\n<p>I have had a longstanding relationship with Lorne and the Surf Coast, returning regularly for over three decades. I now have the opportunity to spend extended time living and working here, allowing my clinical practice to be shaped more directly by our relationship with place and the natural environment.</p>\n<p>Working in a coastal and forested setting offers something distinct from urban practice. Proximity to nature often supports a slower rhythm, greater embodied awareness, and a broader psychological perspective. Where appropriate, psychotherapy in Lorne may also draw on breathwork and nature-based or eco-therapy approaches, supporting a deeper connection to bodily experience and the natural world.﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Approach and&nbsp;Modalities offered:</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p>\n<ul><li><strong><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/psychotherapy-and-counselling\">Psychotherapy</a></strong><br>\nDepth-oriented, trauma-informed psychotherapy for individuals, drawing on relational and embodied approaches.<br>﻿</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/holotropic-breathwork\">One-to-one breathwork</a></strong><br>\nIndividual breathwork sessions offered within a therapeutic framework, supporting emotional processing and nervous system regulation.</p></li><li><p><strong>Breath based&nbsp;somatic approaches&nbsp;<br>﻿</strong>Attention to bodily experience as part of psychological work, supporting integration and embodied awareness.</p></li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Nature-based and eco-therapy approaches</strong><br>\nWhere appropriate, therapeutic work may incorporate the natural environment as a supportive context for reflection and regulation.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Integration-oriented work</strong><br>\nSupport for integrating expanded, altered, or non-ordinary states of consciousness within a grounded psychotherapeutic framework.</p></li></ul>\n<p></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large uk-flex-middle uk-light with-redo height-800px overlay-darkest has-section-width-uk-container-small\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/therapy_ydfwfv&quot;);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-small\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-expand@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"text-align: center;\">Book your first session</h2></div>\n                        </div>                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Whether you’re ready to dive into a full 50-minute psychotherapy session or simply want to start with a short introductory chat to see if this feels like the right fit, you’re welcome to reach out. There’s no pressure or expectation – just an open space to explore what you’re looking for in therapy right now.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can book online or contact me directly if you have questions before committing to a session. I look forward to meeting you and supporting your next steps, whether that’s beginning deep therapeutic work or having an initial conversation to get to know each other.</p></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary mr-4\">﻿Book a session</a><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/book-an-introductory-chat\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary mr-4\">Book an intro chat</a></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'dorin-moise-359008_rbtxt3', 1314, 1, 'I am a Melbourne based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.\nI work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Rd in Brunswick and cater to people looking for support across a wide range of areas including anxiety, depression, spiritual emergence / emergency and more. \n\nI work from a Gestalt-informed, Process Oriented, and Transpersonal perspective, with roots in Traditional Chinese Medicine. My approach is awareness-based, using the breath and body as central tools to support healing and personal growth.\n\nI am a Melbourne based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.\nI work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Rd in Brunswick and cater to people looking for support across a wide range of areas including anxiety, depression, spiritual emergence / emergency and more', 'Wild Heart Psychotherapy – Melbourne Therapy &amp; Breathwork', NULL, 'Melbourne based Psychotherapist and Holotropic Breathwork practitioner offering support for anxiety, depression, and spiritual emergence. Experience healing and personal growth with an awareness-based approach rooted in Traditional Chinese Medicine.', '2026-01-01 03:38:10', '2026-01-05 00:10:31', 0, NULL, 70, NULL, 0, 68, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3091, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Lorne Appointments', 'lorne', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-50 uk-flex-middle with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large row-columns-1-1\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Book an appointment in Lorne</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Sessions are available <strong>in person in Lorne</strong> on the Surf Coast of Victoria. If you are looking for sessions in <strong>Brunswick (Melbourne)</strong> or via <strong>telehealth (Zoom)</strong>, please visit the <a data-start=\"423\" data-end=\"496\" rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/brunswick\">Brunswick booking page</a> for availability.</p>\n<p>Psychotherapy sessions in Lorne can be booked for <strong>50 minutes</strong> or <strong>1 hour 20 minutes</strong>. If you’re not yet ready to book a full session, you’re welcome to schedule a <strong>free 20-minute introductory conversation</strong> to ask questions and explore whether this work feels like a good fit.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in <strong>one-to-one breathwork</strong>, please book an initial <strong>50-minute session</strong>. This session is used to orient the work, discuss suitability, and answer any questions. If appropriate, we will then schedule a <strong>three-hour breathwork session</strong> at a later time.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://app.acuityscheduling.com/schedule.php?owner=34409969&amp;calendarID=13302668&amp;ref=embedded_csp\" title=\"\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"payment\" aria-expanded=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe></figure></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'therapy_ydfwfv', 1314, 1, '', 'Book Your Psychotherapy and Breathwork Sessions in Lorne, Victoria', NULL, 'Schedule your in-person psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork sessions in Lorne, Victoria. Opt for a free 20-minute introductory conversation or book a full session. Also available via telehealth in Brunswick.', '2026-01-02 00:16:29', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 3, NULL, 71, NULL, 0, 14, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3092, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Brunswick Appointments', 'brunswick', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex height-50 uk-flex-middle with-redo padding-medium has-section-width-uk-container-large row-columns-1-1\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container uk-container-large\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        \n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">Appointments In Brunswick</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Sessions are available <strong>in person in Brunswick (Melbourne)</strong> or via <strong>telehealth (Zoom)</strong>. If you are looking for sessions in <strong>Lorne on the Surf Coast</strong>, please visit the <a data-start=\"501\" data-end=\"566\" rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\">Lorne booking page</a> for availability.</p>\n<p>Psychotherapy sessions in Brunswick can be booked for <strong>50 minutes</strong> or <strong>1 hour 20 minutes</strong>. If you’re not yet ready to book a full session, you’re welcome to schedule a <strong>free 20-minute introductory conversation</strong> to ask questions and explore whether this work feels like a good fit.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in <strong>one-to-one breathwork</strong>, please book an initial <strong>50-minute session</strong>. This session is used to orient the work, discuss suitability, and answer any questions. If appropriate, we will then schedule a <strong>three-hour breathwork session</strong> at a later time.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe src=\"https://app.acuityscheduling.com/schedule.php?owner=34409969&amp;calendarID=11313839&amp;ref=embedded_csp\" title=\"\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\" frameborder=\"0\" aria-expanded=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe></figure></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n            </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, 0, '1', '', 'therapy_ydfwfv', 1314, 1, '', 'Brunswick Psychotherapy & Breathwork Sessions | Telehealth Available', NULL, 'Book your psychotherapy or breathwork session in Brunswick, Melbourne or via telehealth. Offering 50-minute sessions, 1 hour 20-minute sessions, or a free 20-minute introductory conversation for new clients.', '2026-01-02 00:23:32', '2026-01-05 00:10:28', 3, NULL, 72, NULL, 0, 13, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3094, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Finding psychotherapy in Lorne', 'finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 row-columns-1-3 padding-none has-section-width-uk-container with-redo\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/jessica-vas-LHZD_gXlLNg-unsplash_dd36um\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"4tbfu72way1w\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary w-full\" target=\"_blank\">﻿BOOK A SESSION</a></p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><section><h1>Lorne Psychotherapy and Counselling</h1><h2>From February 2026, I will be offering Surf Coast psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork sessions in Lorne, Victoria.</h2>\n<p>\nAlongside my Melbourne practice in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick\">Brunswick</a>, this expands my work into the surrounds of the Erskine River rainforest, providing a quieter regional setting for depth-oriented psychotherapy and individual breathwork.</p>\n<p>I have had a longstanding relationship with Lorne and the Surf Coast, returning regularly for over three decades. I now have the opportunity to spend extended time living and working here, allowing my clinical practice to be shaped more directly by our relationship with place and the natural environment.</p>\n<p>Working in a coastal and forested setting offers something distinct from urban practice. Proximity to nature often supports a slower rhythm, greater embodied awareness, and a broader psychological perspective.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Where appropriate, <b>psychotherapy in Lorne</b> may also draw on breathwork and nature-based or eco-therapy approaches, supporting a deeper connection to bodily experience and the natural world.<br></p>\n</section></div>\n                        </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Services offered</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/psychotherapy-and-counselling\">﻿Psychotherapy &amp; Counselling</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/holotropic-breathwork\">One-to-One Breathwork</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/couples-breathwork-therapy-sessions\">Couples Breathwork</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/mens-groups\">Mens Groups</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/retrievals-and-dispatches\">Retrieval and Dispatches</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/psychedelic-integration\">Psychedelic Integration</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><section><h1><strong>Location &amp; Practical Info:</strong>&nbsp;</h1>\n<p>Sessions are held 5 minutes from the Lorne town centre on the road to the Erskine River Waterfall. The therapy room has a sweeping view of the Erskine river forest and stretches out towards the ocean towards Point Addis.&nbsp;</p><p>Parking is available in the main street of Cora Lynn Crt before turning into the drive. Please<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/contact\"> contact me</a> if you have questions about arrival or scheduling.</p>\n<figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d49794.626404592214!2d143.91063760523758!3d-38.53154232159068!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x6ad3653a2508d14d%3A0xf36e7ab931454e69!2sUnit%206%2F5%20Cora%20Lynn%20Ct%2C%20Lorne%20VIC%203232!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sau!4v1767493038798!5m2!1sen!2sau\" width=\"750\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe></figure></section></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><section><h1><strong>Booking:</strong>&nbsp;</h1><p>Sessions can be scheduled via the main <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\">Lorne booking page</a>, or if you would like to find out more you can schedule a <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/book-an-introductory-chat\">free 20 minute exploratory call</a>.</p></section></div>\n                        </div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2025-07-03 07:13:46', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'jessica-vas-LHZD_gXlLNg-unsplash_dd36um', 1314, 1, 'Offering depth-oriented psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork in Lorne, Victoria. Sessions may include somatic and nature-based approaches for adults seeking clarity and growth.', 'Lorne Psychotherapy | Surf Coast Counselling &amp; Breathwork Sessions', NULL, 'Offering depth-oriented psychotherapy and one-to-one breathwork in Lorne, Victoria. Sessions may include somatic and nature-based approaches for adults seeking clarity and growth.', '2026-01-02 05:49:10', '2026-01-05 00:10:29', 0, NULL, 74, NULL, 0, 20, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3096, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'Footer Article', 'footer-article', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex uk-flex-top height-30 padding-large has-section-width-uk-container row-columns-1-4_3-4 uk-dark\" style=\"background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 image-block content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n        	<img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/anthony-avatar-large-anthony-olsen-1080x675_xmdgo9_ynyj1z_5f2vrU_ouiqt4\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"jdvt2la998e2\">\n        </figure></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n    <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n        <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n            <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">About Anthony Olsen</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>My work is informed by Gestalt, Process Oriented, and Transpersonal psychotherapy, with roots in Traditional Chinese Medicine. It is awareness-based and attends to breath, body, and relational experience as central elements of the therapeutic process. This work supports psycho-spiritual integration, meaningful relationships, and a deeper sense of connection to self and others.</p></div>\n            </div>\n        <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p><a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/brunswick\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary uk-margin-small-right\">﻿BOOK A SESSION IN BRUNSWICK</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/lorne\" class=\"uk-button btn uk-button-primary\">BOOK A SESSION IN Lorne&nbsp;</a></p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>Or if you\'d like to find out if we are a good fit or I offer what you are looking for<br> feel free to <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/appointments/book-an-introductory-chat\">book a free 20 minute exploratory call</a>.</p></div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n</div></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2026-01-04 23:16:35', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'elijah-hail-33902_1_lafrye', 1314, 1, '', 'Footer Article', NULL, '', '2026-01-04 23:16:43', '2026-01-05 00:10:31', 0, NULL, 75, NULL, 0, 69, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3097, 1314, 857, 1314, 1314, 1, 'About', 'about', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex padding-large with-redo row-columns-1-3_2-3 has-section-width-uk-container\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1314/anthony-avatar-large-anthony-olsen-1080x675_xmdgo9_ynyj1z_5f2vrU_ouiqt4\" data-image=\"vlq5270ypvat\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><blockquote style=\"margin: 30px 0px 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 30px 0px 0px;\">In the middle of the road of my life, I awoke in a dark wood, where the true way was wholly lost.</blockquote></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p style=\"margin: 0px; text-align: right;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px; text-align: right;\">- David Whyte</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\" style=\"margin: 0px;\">I am a Melbourne &amp; ﻿Surfcoast based Psychotherapist, Holotropic Breathwork practitioner and Men\'s Group facilitator.</h2>\n<p>I ﻿work from a therapy clinic on Sydney Road in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-brunswick\">Brunswick</a> and, from February 2026, will also be offering psychotherapy and individual breathwork sessions in <a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/finding-psychotherapy-in-lorne\">Lorne on the Surf Coast of Victoria</a>. I support people across a wide range of areas, including anxiety, depression, and experiences of spiritual emergence or emergency.</p>\n<p>My work is informed by Gestalt, Process Oriented, and Transpersonal approaches, with roots in Traditional Chinese Medicine. My approach is awareness-based, using the breath and body as central tools to support psychological healing and personal growth.</p>\n<p>I have been involved in the fields of healing and personal development since the mid-1990s. My early work explored how environmental and contextual factors influence health, leading to a period of teaching Western Geomancy at the Australian College of Environmental Studies. There I offered <em>Power of Place</em> field trips and lectures, using experiential methods to deepen awareness of our relationship with place and country.</p>\n<p>A sustained relationship with nature has been an important influence on my work for over two decades and continues to inform a grounded, respectful, and embodied approach to psychotherapy—particularly in regional and coastal settings such as Lorne.﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>\n                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Psychotherapy</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>I offer one-on-one psychotherapy and counselling in Brunswick, and from February 2026, in Lorne on the Surf Coast. My work draws on Gestalt, Process-Oriented, and Transpersonal approaches, using mind, body, and awareness-based practices to support psychological healing, personal growth, and more fulfilling relationships.﻿</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/psychotherapy-and-counselling\">Find out more about Psychotherapy →</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Holotropic Breathwork</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>In the late 1990\'s I had my first experience of Holotropic breathwork, with one of Australia\'s pioneering Holotropic Breathwork practitioners, the Reverend Alf Foote. Alf Foote was a part of the key month-long workshops at the Esalen community during the 1980\'s when Stan Grof started to form the set and setting for Holotropic Breathwork.</p>\n<p>In 2006 I began the Grof Transpersonal Facilitator Training under Tav Sparks and in 2013 certified as a Holotropic Breathwork Facilitor. Since then I have been running regular <a href=\"http://melbournebreathwork.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Holotropic Breathwork workshops in Melbourne</a>.﻿</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/holotropic-breathwork\">Find out more about Holotropic Breathwork →</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Mens Groups</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>I am also keenly interested in working in groups and working with Men to help facilitate greater personal and relational intimacy. I am personally a member of a group that has been meeting monthly for almost 15 years and have also facilitated groups since 2013.</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://wildheartpsychotherapy.com.au/services/experiential-mens-groups\">Find out more about Men\'s Groups →</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"\" tabindex=\"-1\"><hr></figure></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>Music for Breathwork</h2></div>\n</div><div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block new-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p>One of my keen passions is music and in particular music for expanded states of awareness. Over the last 8 years I&nbsp;﻿have been compiling a catalogue of tracks suitable for use as&nbsp;music for breathwork. The <a href=\"https://musicforbreathwork.com/\">Music for breathwork website</a>&nbsp;contains 1600+ tracks that are all tagged based on their relevant uses for breathwork music. In the last year or so I have developed a platform that allows users to create and curate their own playlists either manually or automatically based on the built in tagging system.</p>\n<p>﻿﻿<a href=\"https://musicforbreathwork.com/\">Check out Music for Breathwork →</a>﻿</p></div>\n</div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2026-01-05 00:00:33', NULL, 0, '1', '', 'norway_k1dqti', 1314, 1, '', 'Psychotherapy &amp; Holotropic Breathwork Practitioner in Melbourne &amp; Surfcoast', NULL, 'Melbourne &amp; Surf Coast Psychotherapist &amp; Holotropic Breathwork practitioner, providing healing and personal growth for anxiety, depression, and spiritual emergencies.', '2026-01-05 00:00:49', '2026-01-05 01:36:14', 0, NULL, 76, NULL, 0, 2, NULL, 0, '');
